1
Hello, there. Paradise Court, please.
你好啊 去天堂院 谢谢

2
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:16,879
Paradise Court, coming right up.
天堂院 上车就走

3
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:18,399
Madam...
您请

4
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,840
Thank you.
谢谢

5
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:49,440
Del.
Del

6
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,680
Oi! What are you doing?!
喂 会不会开车啊

7
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,919
-Thank you.  -Enjoy your stay.
-谢谢  -入住愉快

8
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:48,960
Bye.
再见

9
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:53,599
Mr and Mrs Appleby, I presume.
我想您二位一定是Appleby夫妇了

10
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:54,759
That's us.
没错

11
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:57,319
-Welcome to paradise!  -Oh, very nice.
-欢迎到天堂来  -哦 真好

12
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:58,439
Thank you.
谢谢你

13
00:02:58,440 --> 00:02:59,759
Good, good, good.
很好 很好 很好

14
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:01,240
Come, come, follow me.
来 这边 跟我来

15
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,199
Goodnight.
晚安

16
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:24,719
Oh, yes. Goodnight.
哦 好的 晚安

17
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,320
And, er, thank you.
还有 呃 谢谢你

18
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,679
There you are!
终于出来了

19
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,879
It's a wonder you hear anything with that racket.
开那么大声你还听得见真是神了

20
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:08,679
Well, don't just stand gawping, fetch my bags in.
得了 别傻站着 把我的包拿进去

21
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,359
And don't give him too much of a tip.
也别给他太多小费

22
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:12,519
I'm sure he brought us the long way round.
我敢肯定他绕路了

23
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:15,120
And found every pothole along the way!
而且颠得要命

24
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:21,199
Clytemnestra's a friend of yours, is she?
这位慈禧太后是你朋友吗

25
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,759
A relative. My stepmother.
亲戚 我的继母

26
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:26,679
My condolences. Talk about a backseat driver.
为你默哀 她真是个爱指手画脚的人

27
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:29,159
It was too fast. It was too slow.
这样太快了 这样太慢了

28
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:31,519
-The cab was too hot.  -Yeah, that sounds about right.
-车里太热了  -对 她就是这个样子

29
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:33,439
I can take it from here. How much do I, er...?
放在这里我拿就行了 我要付你多少 呃

30
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:34,480
Let me just check.
让我看一下

31
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:39,440
With the excess, that'll be...
算上超额的部分 应该是

32
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:43,039
-..75 of your new English pence.  -Here you go.
-75新便士  -给

33
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:45,159
Take 80. Think of it as danger money.
80你拿去 就当精神损失费了

34
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,320
Ta very much.
多谢了

35
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:02,279
-Did you get it all in?  -Just about.
-都拿进来了吗  -差不多了

36
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:04,159
Just make sure you put it somewhere safe.
一定要找地方放好

37
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:06,640
-The rest arrives tomorrow.  -The rest?
-剩下的明天到  -还有剩下的

38
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:09,799
Well, didn't you get my letter?
你没收到我的信吗

39
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:12,320
I've sold the house and bought a place in Eynsham.
我把房子卖了 在Eynsham买了个新的

40
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:14,799
Joyce has got herself engaged
Joyce订婚了

41
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,119
to some man she's living in sin with at Witney.
跟她那个在Witney同居的姘头

42
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,719
Oh, she never mentioned.
哦 她没提过

43
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:21,040
Well, who's to blame for that if you don't keep in touch?
谁让你不跟我们联系呢

44
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:24,240
Keith Garrett, his name is.
他叫Keith Garrett

45
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,599
Couldn't you stay with them?
你不能跟他们一起住吗

46
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,400
Do you think I'd be here if I could?
如果能我还来这儿干什么

47
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:33,519
They're abroad until Wednesday.
他们出国了 周三才回来

48
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:36,919
Unmarried and both in the same room.
没结婚 还住一个屋

49
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:39,279
Hm! It's not right.
哼 没规矩

50
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,199
But what about a hotel?
那怎么不去住宾馆呢

51
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:43,759
Well, you'll be all right on the sofa for a couple of nights.
你就在沙发上凑合几个晚上又不会有问题

52
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:46,519
I mean, I don't like it any more than you do.
我也不情愿来跟你住

53
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:49,120
-It's only till I take possession.  -When's that?
-房子办好手续就走  -哪天

54
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:53,279
There is no need to ask in that tone.
没必要用这种口气问吧

55
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:56,360
I am not one of your interrogation suspects.
我又不是你的犯罪嫌疑人

56
00:06:58,640 --> 00:06:59,919
Monday.
周一

57
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:02,039
But you don't have to worry about me.
但是你不需要操心我

58
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:04,039
I don't expect to be looked after.
我也不用你照顾

59
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:06,000
Ha! You won't even know I'm here.
哈 你甚至都感觉不到我在这

60
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:17,880
If you could give your statement to my colleague over here.
请我的这位同事给你录一下口供

61
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:24,599
It looks to be robbery. Wallet's empty.
像是抢劫 钱包空了

62
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:27,919
Dudley Lunn, according to the Speedy Cabs office.
死者Dudley Lunn 极速出租车提供的信息

63
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,319
42.
42岁

64
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:32,359
Married. Uniform's notifying his wife now.
已婚 警员正在通知他的妻子

65
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:34,800
The paperboy came upon the car just after 6:00.
报童6点的时候发现的车子

66
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,480
Doctor.
法医

67
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:43,119
Do we know how long he's been there?
他在这大概多久了

68
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,599
Rigor well established,
尸僵很严重

69
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:47,840
which, as well as making my labours more difficult...
让我的工作难上加难

70
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:51,879
..suggests he's been dead about 12 hours.
他死了大概有12小时了

71
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:54,799
Are we sure about that, the time of death?
你确定吗 死亡时间

72
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:59,759
The glass on his watch is cracked and the hands are set to 6:50.
他的手表碎了 指针停在了6:50

73
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:04,120
Then the watch stopped ticking several hours before Mr Lunn did.
那他的表就比Lunn先生早寿终正寝了几个小时

74
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:07,439
The body doesn't lie, Morse.
尸体不会说谎 Morse

75
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,799
Myself notwithstanding,
我还是相信

76
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:13,920
it's the only impartial, reliable witness to any suspicious death.
死者是任何非自然死亡中唯一公正可靠的证人

77
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,799
So, ten-ish last night, then.
那就是昨晚十点多了

78
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:19,439
Mm, by my reckoning, yes.
嗯 我估计差不多

79
00:08:19,440 --> 00:08:21,599
Single shot to the back of the skull.
从后脑开了一枪

80
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,919
Point-blank range.
近距离射击

81
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:27,359
Exit wound just above the left eye.
子弹射出口就在左眼上缘

82
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,799
As you can see...
你能看到

83
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:34,159
..the bullet strikes the windscreen, drops onto the dash.
子弹击中了前挡风玻璃 掉在了仪表盘上

84
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:36,800
Et voila
瞧

85
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:41,639
Looks to be a .22, but it has taken quite a battering.
看起来是22口径的 但是严重变形

86
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:45,439
I'll be able to give you the def gen after the postmortem.
尸检之后才能给你确切信息

87
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,879
Shall we say 2:30?
我们约两点半吧

88
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:49,999
It's late for you, Doctor.
这比你平时要久啊 医生

89
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,320
Steak and kidney at The Eagle.
要去老鹰酒吧吃牛排和腰子

90
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,680
I wouldn't want to rush that dissection.
我可不想吃得匆匆忙忙

91
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,680
A cabbie's about as easy a mark as it gets.
出租司机有一个很典型的特征

92
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:05,639
They have to go out with a decent float,
他们出门的时候一定会揣着一大堆零钱

93
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:07,880
and it'll only get bigger as the shift goes on.
拉过几单客人之后只会越来越多

94
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,799
There was a driver a couple of weeks ago,
几个礼拜之前有个司机

95
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,559
on our old ground, got put in hospital.
在我们的旧辖区 被送进了医院

96
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,119
Pistol-whipped.
被枪托打晕了

97
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:17,439
From what he could remember, the suspect was bearded, dark-haired.
据他回忆 嫌疑人有胡子 深发色

98
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:19,199
-Speedy Cabs again?  -No.
-也是极速出租车吗  -不是

99
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,720
A2B Cars out of Cowley.
是从考利出发的A2B出租

100
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:23,759
It's a long way to drive to kill someone, isn't it?
杀人倒也不用跑这么远吧

101
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:25,159
Yeah.
是啊

102
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:27,279
Private, though. No witnesses.
但这里很私密 没有目击者

103
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:29,319
Well, that's fine, as far as it goes.
到这一步也没什么问题

104
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:32,119
But if he kills his ride, how's he gonna get back?
但是如果他杀了司机 要怎么回去

105
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:34,079
Maybe he didn't have to.
或许他不需要回去

106
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,439
Carry on down the lane aways,
沿着小路往下走

107
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:37,360
there's a place called Paradise Court.
有个地方叫天堂院

108
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,760
Some sort of naturist camp.
是个天体主义者的大本营

109
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,960
For nudists.
裸露癖

110
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:45,279
That's where the paperboy was for.
报童就是要去那儿的

111
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:46,760
What have you got there?
你捡到什么了

112
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:50,599
-A piece of old tissue?  -All right, matey, don't rub it in.
-一片旧布料吗  -别老戳人痛处 老兄

113
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:52,159
We haven't all got your eye.
又不是人人都有你那么尖的眼睛

114
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:54,399
I just thought it might've been something, is all.
我只是想可能是个什么 就捡来看看

115
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,319
Best bag it in any case.
以防万一还是装起来

116
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:58,959
We'll talk to the family and have a word with his work.
我们去跟他的家人和工作单位聊一聊

117
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:02,359
Do you want to see if anyone heard anything up at that...
你能不能去那个地方问问有没有人

118
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,840
..place?
听见动静

119
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:21,119
When he didn't come home,
他没回家的时候

120
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,560
I thought maybe he'd had a long fare, you know?
我还在想他是不是去跑长途了

121
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:27,119
Somebody might want him to take them to Grimsby.
有人可能想打车去Grimsby

122
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:28,760
Or anywhere you care to think of.
或者其他哪里

123
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:32,720
I did say that to the constables who came by earlier.
我跟先前来过的警官说过了

124
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:36,839
I thought they would have written it down in their notebook or somewhere.
我以为他们都记下来了

125
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,080
But they didn't.
但是他们没有

126
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:41,680
I'm afraid that's our job, Mrs Lunn.
恐怕这是我们的活儿 Lunn夫人

127
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,320
I'm sorry to have to ask, but...
很抱歉但我得问

128
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:48,559
..all was well at home, was it?
家里没什么矛盾吧

129
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:49,840
Oh, yes.
哦 没有

130
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:53,040
Ours was a very happy marriage.
我们婚姻很和谐

131
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:57,759
Fenella will be heartbroke.
Fenella一定难过死了

132
00:10:57,760 --> 00:10:59,640
She's out playing right now, but...
她现在在外面玩儿呢 但

133
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:02,520
..she idolises her father.
她很崇拜她的父亲

134
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,359
You will tell Pauline, will you?
你们会通知Pauline吗

135
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,959
Or have I got to do that?
还是得我去说

136
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:10,320
Who's Pauline?
谁是Pauline

137
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:14,159
He was married before.
他的前妻

138
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,879
She lives in Headington.
住在Headington

139
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:17,680
There's a kiddie, a boy.
他们有一个男孩

140
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,439
She'll have to be told.
如果要告诉她

141
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:22,760
And she won't thank me for it, will she?
她也不会感谢我的 对吧

142
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:28,000
I think it's probably better coming from you.
我觉得最好是你们去说

143
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:34,040
Good afternoon, sir.
下午好 先生

144
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:37,839
Luggage in the car, is it?
您的行李在车上吗

145
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:39,599
No, it's, er...
没有 呃

146
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:43,079
First visit? Well, there's no need to be nervous.
第一次来吗 不必紧张

147
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,320
No need at all.
完全不用

148
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:48,559
Now, I don't think we've any reservation down for today.
我看我们没有今天的预约

149
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,839
But we've plenty of vacancies.
但是还有不少空房

150
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,519
The season hasn't really got going yet.
旺季还没开始呢

151
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:52,920
I'm a policeman.
我是警察

152
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:57,760
And I'm a former major with the Argyll and Sutherland Highlanders.
那我还是阿盖尔与萨瑟兰高地步兵团的前少校军官呢

153
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:02,839
But the naturist world takes us as it finds us, Mr...?
但是天体主义者的世界待我们一视同仁 怎么称呼

154
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:05,520
Detective Sergeant Strange, Thames Valley.
Strange警长 泰晤士河谷警局

155
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:09,200
And I'm not here for a frolic in the altogether, Major...?
我不是来这里裸体嗨皮的 少校

156
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,840
Jones.
Jones

157
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,600
Ahem!
咳咳

158
00:12:27,640 --> 00:12:30,439
If I could have everyone's attention for a moment.
抱歉占用大家几分钟

159
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:34,119
-This is, er...  -Detective Sergeant Strange, Thames Valley.
-这位是 呃  -泰晤士河谷警局的Strange警长

160
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:37,000
If you wouldn't mind putting something on while I talk to you.
劳驾各位在跟我说话的时候先穿上衣服

161
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,479
Thank you.
谢谢

162
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:51,279
Now, I must ask if any of you saw or heard anything unusual last night.
我要请问昨晚你们有没有看见或听见什么异常

163
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:54,479
I did say, Sergeant, with the music from the luau...
要我说 警长 夏威夷风情宴会放着音乐的时候

164
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:56,799
-Like a gunshot, you mean?  -Perhaps.
-比如说枪声吗  -之类的

165
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:59,039
-Miss...?  -Appleby.
-小姐您叫  -Appleby

166
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,959
Alison Appleby, Mrs.
Alison Appleby夫人

167
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:02,520
I thought it was a car backfiring.
我以为是辆车引擎回火了

168
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:04,719
Barry Appleby.
我叫Barry Appleby.

169
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:05,839
Baz.
叫我Baz

170
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:07,439
What time would that have been?
那大概是几点

171
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:09,799
The guests all turn their watches in upon arrival
客人们到这里时都把手表上交了

172
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:12,399
as part of the process of getting back to nature.
这是回归自然过程的一部分

173
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:16,079
That's true, but I heard the church clock chime ten shortly after.
没错 但是没过多久我就听到教堂敲了十点的钟声

174
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:18,040
Right.
好的

175
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:28,519
-No need to go to all that trouble, Mrs Lunn.  -It's no trouble.
-不用麻烦了 Lunn太太  -不麻烦

176
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:30,719
And Pauline, please.
叫我Pauline吧

177
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:32,439
I only get called Mrs Lunn
只有律师 社工

178
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:35,879
by solicitors or the Social or up at Mark's school.
或者Mark学校里的人才叫我Lunn太太

179
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:38,959
Cowley Secondary Modern? I thought I recognised the uniform.
Cowley现代中学 我好像认得这个校服

180
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,959
-My two went there.  -Oh, yeah?
-我的两个孩子也去那上过学  -是吗

181
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:43,279
-When was that?  -Oh, a long time past.
-什么时候  -好久之前了

182
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,879
The youngest, my boy, is in the Army now out in Ireland.
我的小儿子现在去了爱尔兰当兵

183
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:49,439
And my daughter, well, she's with the Welfare looking after kids.
我女儿在福利部门照顾孩子

184
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:51,239
I probably know her.
我也许认得她

185
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,239
Mark's got into trouble once or twice.
Mark惹过一两次麻烦

186
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,919
He's not a bad boy.
他不是坏孩子

187
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:56,439
He just misses his dad.
只是想爸爸了

188
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,959
God knows what this will do to him.
天知道这会对他产生什么影响

189
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:01,040
I'm sorry for asking, but, er...
不好意思我问一下

190
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:04,599
-..you are divorced, I take it?  -Oh, yeah.
-你应该是离婚了吧  -是的

191
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:06,559
Four years, last February.
之前二月份的时候就满四年了

192
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:09,599
Ann is the official Mrs Lunn now. I'm...
现在Ann是正式的Lunn太太 我是

193
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:12,199
Well, I don't know what you'd call it. What would it be?
不知道你们是怎么叫的 该怎么说呢

194
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,240
The dowager Mrs Lunn?
前Lunn太太

195
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:16,839
-He gambled, did he?  -Gambled?
-他赌博吗  -赌博

196
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:19,799
If it had four legs, he couldn't throw money after it fast enough.
只要是有四条腿的 他迫不及待追着扔钱

197
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:22,480
That and... Well, you've met her.
而且 你们见过她了

198
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:25,559
How did he meet the second Mrs Lunn?
他是怎么遇见第二任Lunn太太的

199
00:14:25,560 --> 00:14:28,999
Oh, didn't she say? She worked in the cab office.
她没说吗 她在出租车公司做文职

200
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,159
On the radio, handing out the jobs.
负责广播 分派任务

201
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:32,719
It started there.
就是从那里开始的

202
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,199
They usually fizzled out.
她们基本上都不长久

203
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:37,759
Only, he got her in the family way and, well...
但是他让她怀了孩子 然后

204
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:39,720
You said, they usually.
你说 她们基本上

205
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:44,600
With Dudley it was four legs, good, two legs, better.
对于Dudley来说 四条腿的动物好赌 两条腿的人更好玩

206
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,719
I tried to keep it from Mark as best I could,
我尽量不让Mark知道这些事

207
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:49,680
but children pick up on things, don't they?
但孩子们总是很敏感 对吧

208
00:15:30,040 --> 00:15:31,880
All right, then, see you back at base.
好的 回公司见

209
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:36,399
45, 45, pick up 52 Festive Avenue
45 45 到52节日大道接人

210
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:39,039
going to Headington on account.
送去Headington 记账的

211
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,759
A Mr Benn.
Benn先生

212
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,719
No, it's just awful news.
这事儿太可怕了

213
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:43,959
Awful.
太可怕了

214
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:45,759
You heard about what happened
你听说了A2B出租车公司

215
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:48,199
to the driver from A2B Cars, presumably?
那个司机的事了吗

216
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,279
The fellas have been talking about nothing else.
那家伙把这事儿翻来覆去地说

217
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:52,560
You hope it's just a one-off. But now this?
还希望是一次性的 但现在又出了这事

218
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:55,599
Puts the fear of God in everyone.
大家全都胆战心惊的

219
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,999
Oh, sorry about this. Got to answer it.
不好意思 这个得接一下

220
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,639
Usually, we've a girl, but it's her afternoon off.
一般都是个姑娘接 但今天她歇班

221
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:03,479
Speedy Cabs, can I help you?
极速出租车 您有什么需要

222
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:05,400
Hello?
喂

223
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:09,360
Oh, yeah, that's my Siwan.
哦 这是我家Siwan

224
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:12,559
Joan, she'd be in English.
英文名叫Joan

225
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:15,319
Though most everybody calls her Birdie.
不过别人都叫她Birdie

226
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,919
Fy nghyw bach.
我的小姑娘（威尔士语）

227
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:20,399
Always singing round the house, she is. Like a cock linnet.
总是在家里唱歌 像只百灵鸟

228
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:21,880
Beautiful.
很漂亮

229
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:25,439
-Have you got kids?  -Yeah, two, as it happens.
-你有孩子吗  -对 有两个

230
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:28,519
Speedy Cabs, how can I help you?
极速出租车 您有什么需要

231
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:31,199
Erm, yeah. What time would you like that for?
行 您希望是几点呢

232
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,319
Oh, our pleasure.
不客气

233
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,839
Thank you, now.
谢谢

234
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,279
Goodbye.
再见

235
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:39,519
Did you give him a job to Hovelle Wood last night?
昨晚你给他派了去Hovelle树林的活吗

236
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:41,319
Paradise Court, perhaps.
也可能是天堂院

237
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:43,560
That's where it happened, is it?
就是在那里出的事 是吗

238
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:47,840
Er, no, erm, well, the last dispatch I had for...
呃 没有 我最后一次给

239
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:51,119
..for Dudley was... Let me see now. It's all in here, see?
Dudley派活 我看看 都记在这上面 你看

240
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:53,439
Oh, yeah, here it is, look.
对 在这里 你看

241
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:57,279
5:18 pick up. Summertown to Beaufort.
5点18分接的 从Summertown去Beaufort

242
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,440
Dr Hu.
Hu博士

243
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:00,959
Oriental studies.
研究东方学的

244
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,640
Old boy, one of our regulars.
老朋友了 是我们的常客

245
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:05,479
And there was nothing after that?
在那之后没有了吗

246
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:07,519
Well, if there was, it didn't come from me.
如果有的话 也不是我分派的

247
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:10,159
Oh, I had a word with the boys.
我跟兄弟们聊过了

248
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:14,640
A couple of the lads said he was on the rank at Cowley East last night.
有几个人说他昨晚在考利东区趴活

249
00:17:19,320 --> 00:17:21,279
Do you want some tanning butter?
要擦美黑油吗

250
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:23,520
-No.  -You don't want to burn.
-不用  -别晒伤了

251
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:29,199
Where did you get to last night?
你昨晚去哪了

252
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,079
I woke up and you weren't there.
我醒的时候你不在

253
00:17:31,080 --> 00:17:33,719
-Call of nature.  -You were ever such a long time.
-人有三急  -你也去了太长时间吧

254
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:35,319
Yes, well, I couldn't find it.
对 我找不到厕所

255
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:37,359
Maybe I should've said...
我是不是应该说出来

256
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:39,079
..that we'd just come by taxi.
我们是坐出租车来的

257
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:40,879
You don't think it was our driver, do you?
应该不是我们的司机吧 你觉得呢

258
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:42,559
No, why would it be?
不是 怎么可能

259
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:44,679
He dropped us off at 7:30.
他七点半把我们送到

260
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:46,919
You said yourself, you heard the gunshot around 10:00.
你自己也说 10点左右听到枪响

261
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,279
If that's what you did hear.
如果你真的有听到

262
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:51,879
He's hardly likely to hang around at the top of the lane all that time.
那段时间他不可能一直在路这头闲逛吧

263
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:53,959
Was it the top of the lane?
是在路这头出的事吗

264
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:56,079
Oh, I don't know, do I? I'm just guessing.
我不知道啊 我猜的

265
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:57,799
Anyway, you don't want to get involved.
反正 别被卷进去了

266
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:00,799
I wish that man would go and clip his privets elsewhere.
我希望那个人去别的地方修枝

267
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:02,280
He's staring!
他盯着我们看

268
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:09,959
8:30, 8:45. Something like that is about the last time we saw him.
8：30 8：45 我们最后一次见他大概就是那时候

269
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:12,320
-Wouldn't you say, Brian?  -Yeah, that's right.
-你说呢 Brian  -对 没错

270
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:17,199
Dudley was at the, er, top of the rank waiting for a fare.
趴活等客人的队伍里 Dudley排第一个

271
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,119
Did you see who got into the cab?
你看见上车的人是谁了吗

272
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:20,359
Er, no.
没有

273
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:23,079
Did either of you have a job out to Hovelle Wood last night?
昨晚你们有人载客去Hovelle树林吗

274
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:25,279
-Hovelle Wood?  -Mm-hm.
-Hovelle树林  -嗯

275
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:27,720
-No, sir, no.  -All right, fellas?
-没有 警官  -怎么样 兄弟们

276
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:31,639
-What's all this?  -The police, Joe.
-这怎么回事  -警察来了 Joe

277
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:33,359
-It's about Dudley.  -Dudley?
-是Dudley的事  -Dudley

278
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:35,279
-What about him?  -You haven't heard?
-他怎么了  -你没听说吗

279
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:37,359
Oh, my!
天哪

280
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:40,159
He's been murdered, Mr...?
他被谋杀了 你是

281
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,920
North. Joe North.
North Joe North

282
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,079
Here, don't I...?
哎 我不是

283
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:47,519
Yeah, Mr North dropped a fare at my house this morning, sir.
对 今早North先生去我家送了个人 头儿

284
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:50,200
Detective Sergeant Morse. Detective Chief Inspector Thursday.
我是Morse探长 这位是Thursday总警督

285
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:53,920
So... what happened?
出什么事了

286
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:57,279
Not another guy like this fella with A2B
该不会跟A2B公司那个人一样吧

287
00:18:57,280 --> 00:18:59,959
We're keeping an open mind, but it looks that way.
我们还没下定论 但看起来就是这样

288
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:01,679
Here, Clarry, you're up, look.
哎 Clarry 到你了

289
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:04,119
Oh! If you'll excuse me, officers.
哦 失陪了 警官们

290
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:05,759
Certainly, Mr Haynes.
没事 Haynes先生

291
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:07,999
He was keen on the horses, I understand.
听说他热衷赌马

292
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,360
Oh, yes.
对

293
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,759
He was always touching one of us up
他总是找我们

294
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:13,480
for a couple of quid to put on the gee-gees.
借个几块钱押注在马上

295
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:16,999
Right. And he liked women, too, I hear.
嗯 听说他还喜欢女人

296
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:20,200
Well, crumpet in and out the back of the cab all day.
出租车后座上从早到晚那么多浪蹄子进进出出

297
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,560
Can't blame him, can you?
也不怪他 对吧

298
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:25,679
Well, if anything else
如果你们想到了什么

299
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:27,680
should cross your mind, you know where to find us.
就来找我们

300
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:44,440
I can confirm that the bullet which killed Mr Lunn was a .22.
可以确定杀死Lunn先生的子弹是点22口径

301
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:48,279
I've passed it to Ballistics for a full analysis.
我把它交给弹道检测部门做全面分析了

302
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:49,839
Small calibre.
小口径

303
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:51,519
A woman's gun, perhaps?
可能是女式手枪

304
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,839
-Ruth Ellis fired a .38, of course.  -She did.
-Ruth Ellis用的就是点38手枪  -确实

305
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:55,599
But it wasn't hers.
但那不是她的枪

306
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:58,679
You're not gonna want to keep a Smith & Wesson in your handbag
你不可能把大口径手枪和化妆品一起

307
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:00,519
along with your compact, are you?
装在包包里 对吧

308
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:01,719
Anything else?
还有别的吗

309
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:05,399
Nothing to suggest any kind of struggle for the weapon.
没有迹象表明死者曾经抢夺过武器

310
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:08,880
He very likely had no inkling he was about to die.
他很可能完全不知道自己即将被杀害

311
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:11,479
The Ostrich Fanciers' Club.
鸵鸟爱好者俱乐部

312
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:13,159
-Never heard of it.  -No address.
-从没听说过  -没有地址

313
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:15,199
But there is a telephone number on the back.
不过背面有电话号码

314
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:17,639
I'll see if we can get a reverse trace.
我去查查会不会有别的线索

315
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:19,759
What will he have had in his wallet, £10, £15, £20?
他的钱包里本来有多少钱 10镑 15 20

316
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,719
-Would you kill someone for that?  -I've seen people killed for less.
-你会为这点钱杀人吗  -为更少的钱杀人我都见过

317
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:25,159
What are you saying, that emptying the wallet was a blind?
你什么意思 空钱包只是个障眼法

318
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:28,119
Well, unless I'm much mistaken, that's not just blood on his collar.
除非是我搞错了 他领子上不止有血

319
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:29,639
That's lipstick.
还有口红

320
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:31,679
No. If you could keep Fenella with you
不 如果你可以把Fenella带在身边

321
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:33,560
and I'll fetch her on the way back.
我就在回去的路上接她

322
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:39,000
They're sending a car for me to go and do the identifying.
他们派了辆车来接我去辨认

323
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:43,440
I know, I can't believe it myself.
我知道 我都不敢相信

324
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:48,999
I don't know what I'm going to do for her tea.
不知道跟她喝茶的事该怎么办

325
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,239
He was something of a womaniser,
他就像个花花公子

326
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:53,959
according to his mates and the first Mrs Lunn.
根据他的同事还有第一任Lunn太太所说

327
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:55,439
Indeed.
这样啊

328
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:59,080
Morse noted a smudge of bright, red lipstick on his collar.
Morse在他的衣领上发现了一块亮红色的口红污迹

329
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:02,519
Another woman, then?
有另一个女人

330
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:03,760
A jealous husband, perhaps?
也许是个嫉妒的丈夫

331
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,399
Or wife, sir.
或者妻子 长官

332
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:07,920
Or wife.
或者妻子

333
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,919
'We've 20,000 people on the site.
我们现场有两万人

334
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:13,839
-'Without a name, I can't really help you.'  -Right. Understood.
-没有名字 我真的帮不上忙  -好的 明白

335
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:16,240
Well, thank you very much. Sorry to have troubled you.
非常感谢 抱歉打扰了

336
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:22,079
I've conducted some odd interviews in my time, matey.
询问的时候奇怪的事情我也见过一些 兄弟

337
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:24,799
But stone me, this morning's go takes the Garibaldi.
但今早这次 真是震惊他妈给震惊开门 震惊到家了

338
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:27,039
-What's this?  -Paradise Court.
-什么事  -天堂院

339
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:28,319
The nudie place.
那个天体营

340
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:31,399
A couple there think they'd heard a gunshot. A Mr and Mrs Appleby.
那里有对夫妻觉得听到了一声枪响 Appleby夫妇

341
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:34,400
Only, they took it to be a car backfiring just before 10:00.
10点前听到的 不过他们以为那是汽车回火声

342
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:39,359
Lunn picks his fare up outside the station between 8:45 and 9:00,
8点45到9点之间 Lunn在车站外接乘客

343
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:43,479
gets to the Hovelle Wood area between 9:45, 10:00.
9点45到10点之间 到达Hovelle树林

344
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:44,599
That works, more or less.
时间线算是对得上吧

345
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,839
