00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:50,600
# I'm just a fool
# 我只是个傻瓜

532
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:56,759
# A fool in love
# 爱你的

533
00:34:56,760 --> 00:35:02,720
# With you.
# 傻瓜

534
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:20,879
Hey!
嘿

535
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:23,239
Hey, what the hell do you think you're doing?!
嘿 你他妈在想什么

536
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:24,559
I could've killed you!
我也许会撞死你

537
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:28,559
What...? Officer...
什么 警官

538
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:30,360
-..are you OK?  -I'm sorry.
-你还好吗  -抱歉

539
00:35:32,760 --> 00:35:34,399
Come on, sir. Come on, let me help you.
长官 起来吧 站起来 我来帮您

540
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:37,360
Who's this?
你是谁呀

541
00:35:39,120 --> 00:35:41,239
-Are you OK?  -Yeah, I just tripped and...
-您没事吧  -没事 我就是有点儿没站稳

542
00:35:41,240 --> 00:35:43,200
..and missed my footing a little bit.
突然绊了一跤

543
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:47,520
That could have happened to anyone. Which way are you going?
谁都可能会这样 您往哪个方向走啊

544
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:50,199
Erm, this way.
呃 这边

545
00:35:50,200 --> 00:35:52,279
Look, let Clarry take you home safe, sir.
长官 让我开车把您安全送到家吧

546
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:54,720
Come on, the car's there, sir. Come, come.
这边 车在这边 长官 过来吧 来吧

547
00:35:57,760 --> 00:35:59,399
You scared the life out of me, man.
你真是要把我魂吓出来了

548
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:27,200
Thank you.
谢谢

549
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:35,919
Well, listen, thanks for helping me out tonight.
谢谢你今晚帮我

550
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:36,960
You're welcome.
不客气

551
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:41,000
Right, night, then.
那就晚安了

552
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,200
Night.
晚安

553
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:47,959
Blimey.
老天爷呀

554
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:49,479
I won't wash my face for a week now.
我之后一周都不会洗脸了

555
00:36:49,480 --> 00:36:52,039
What was that for?
你为什么笑呀

556
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,800
A lovely evening.
今晚过得很愉快

557
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:57,160
Go on, in you go.
进去吧 快进去

558
00:36:58,560 --> 00:36:59,999
Oh, listen, don't feel like
噢 对了 不用觉得

559
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:02,879
you've got to come to The Carpenters if it's not your...
你必须得去卡彭特乐队演唱会 如果你不感兴趣

560
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:04,439
Excuse me, we won, didn't we?
什么呀 我们赢了 不是吗

561
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:06,359
-Yeah, but...  -A night out in London?
-是 但是  -伦敦一夜游

562
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:08,679
I'm not gonna turn that down.
我可不会拒绝这个

563
00:37:08,680 --> 00:37:10,679
She does have a lovely voice.
她唱歌是很好听的

564
00:37:10,680 --> 00:37:12,280
Yeah, she does.
是的 确实

565
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:17,839
Right, then, goodnight.
好了 那就 晚安

566
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:19,200
Goodnight.
晚安

567
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:36,999
Phwoar!
哇哦

568
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:38,680
Nice bit of crumpet.
这马子真不错

569
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:42,919
She's not crumpet.
她不是马子

570
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:46,240
She's a smart, bright, independent, young woman.
她是位聪颖 开朗 独立的年轻女性

571
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:50,079
You'll remember it if you're looking for a tip next time.
下次想拿到小费的话可要记住了

572
00:37:50,080 --> 00:37:51,560
Whatever you say, squire.
听你的 骑士

573
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:22,719
Are you all right, now?
你现在感觉还行嘛

574
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:24,000
Yep.
还行

575
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:33,200
Thanks for the lift.
谢谢你载我回家

576
00:38:45,240 --> 00:38:46,680
Oh, it's all right, I've got them.
噢 没事了 我找到了

577
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:29,639
Father Francis Mahoney.
Francis Mahoney神父

578
00:39:29,640 --> 00:39:30,840
56.
56岁

579
00:39:31,880 --> 00:39:33,759
-Who found him?  -His housekeeper.
-谁发现的  -他的管家

580
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:35,040
A Mrs Walsh.
Walsh夫人

581
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:38,639
She brought him a cup of tea to his room at the rectory,
她去他教区长住宅的卧室送茶

582
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:40,399
only to find his bed hadn't been slept in.
发现他的床没有睡过的痕迹

583
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:43,519
So, she came in here to look for him.
所以她来这边找他了

584
00:39:43,520 --> 00:39:45,239
She doesn't live in, then?
她是不和神父住一起吗

585
00:39:45,240 --> 00:39:47,159
Goes home of an evening after he's had his tea.
她在神父晚上喝完茶后离开

586
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:49,200
Then comes in first thing to see to his breakfast.
然后一早过来准备早餐

587
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:54,879
Looks to be another robbery, in any event.
不管怎么说 看起来又是一起抢劫案

588
00:39:54,880 --> 00:39:57,519
Wallet's open and empty on the floor of the confessional.
钱包丢在忏悔室的地上 被打开了 里面空空如也

589
00:39:57,520 --> 00:39:59,239
Anything, Doctor?
医生 有什么发现吗

590
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:00,719
I'm afraid Father Mahoney
恐怕Mahoney神父

591
00:40:00,720 --> 00:40:03,600
got rather more of an earful than he was expecting.
听到的忏悔比他想的要多不少

592
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,159
Shot through the screen.
子弹从屏风射过来

593
00:40:06,160 --> 00:40:10,599
Body temperature and rigour suggests he joined the choir invisible
从尸体温度和僵硬程度来判断 他大概14到16小时前就

594
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:13,039
about 14 to 16 hours ago.
离世了

595
00:40:13,040 --> 00:40:16,399
That makes it sometime after last night's seven o'clock mass.
那就是晚上七点弥撒之后发生的啊

596
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:18,279
Doesn't confession happen before mass,
忏悔不应该在弥撒前吗

597
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:20,759
unless it's prearranged with the priest?
除非是牧师提前安排好的

598
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:25,559
There's no exit wound this time, so calibre will have to wait on the PM.
这次不是贯穿伤 所以子弹口径结果要到下午才能出来

599
00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:27,239
Might we remove the body?
我们能把尸体移走吧

600
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:29,359
Of course, Doctor. By any means.
好的 法医 完全没问题

601
00:40:29,360 --> 00:40:31,520
Very well, then. Shall we say two o'clock?
很好 那我们约个两点吧

602
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:39,479
What would a taxi driver and a priest have in common
出租车司机和牧师会有什么共同点

603
00:40:39,480 --> 00:40:41,519
that would be of interest to the same killer?
会让同一个凶手感兴趣

604
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:44,119
Until we have forensics on the bullet, we don't know they were.
弹道鉴定结果出来前 不能判定是同一凶手所为

605
00:40:44,120 --> 00:40:46,599
What, two shootings in two days by two different killers?
什么 两天内两起不同凶手犯下的枪击案

606
00:40:46,600 --> 00:40:48,399
That hardly seems likely, does it?
这好像不太可能吧

607
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:51,319
I went back to Cowley East to talk to the station staff last night.
我昨晚又去了考利东区和店员们聊了聊

608
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:52,599
The waitress at the cafe
咖啡店的服务生说

609
00:40:52,600 --> 00:40:55,599
said a cleric had been in the night that Lunn was killed.
Lunn被杀的那晚有个牧师在那里

610
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:57,279
Hanging about over his coffee.
边喝咖啡边闲逛

611
00:40:57,280 --> 00:41:00,319
-Mahoney?  -One dog collar's much like another.
-是Mahoney吗  -牧师穿得一样 看上去都差不多

612
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:02,759
We'll see if there's any photos of him up at the rectory
我们去教区长房子里看看有没有他的照片

613
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:04,519
-and you can run it past her.  -Right.
-你可以带给她去辨认一下  -好

614
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:06,719
She also said there was a young woman.
她还说那时候还有个年轻女人

615
00:41:06,720 --> 00:41:09,680
Blonde. Twenties. Kept watching the cab rank.
金发 二十多岁 一直在看出租车队

616
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:12,599
Get going with door to door.
你去附近挨家挨户问一下

617
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:14,480
-We'll brace the housekeeper.  -Sir.
-我们去拜访一下管家  -是 长官

618
00:41:19,960 --> 00:41:21,679
What happened to you this morning?
你今天早上怎么回事

619
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:23,480
Oh, I'm sorry, I, er... I missed the alarm.
噢 抱歉 呃 我 我没听见闹钟

620
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:26,160
That shirt looks like you've slept in it.
这衬衫皱得像你昨晚穿着它睡的一样

621
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:29,159
I've got my stepmother staying with me
我继母搬过来和我住了

622
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:30,799
until she moves into a place in Eynsham.
一直到她在Eynsham的房子可以入住

623
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:32,279
I'm on the sofa. It's not ideal.
我在沙发上睡 睡不好

624
00:41:32,280 --> 00:41:34,199
Still no excuse for a grubby shirt.
那也不是衬衫脏兮兮的借口

625
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:36,439
Slovenly dress leads to a slovenly mind.
穿得邋遢 思想就邋遢

626
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:38,719
If more connects these cases than robbery,
如果这两起案子不仅仅是抢劫的话

627
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:40,679
then I'll need you to earn your keep.
我希望你干的活对得起你挣的钱

628
00:41:40,680 --> 00:41:42,479
Well, I wasn't completely idle last night.
我昨晚并不是什么都没干

629
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:43,919
I went back to where Lunn was shot.
我又去了一趟Lunn的案发现场

630
00:41:43,920 --> 00:41:45,559
I almost went the same way myself.
差点就落得和Lunn一样的下场了

631
00:41:45,560 --> 00:41:48,200
His son was lying in wait in case the killer returned to the scene.
他儿子就在那儿等着 等着凶手重回案发现场

632
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:51,319
-You mean, he was armed?  -Yeah, a .22 pistol.
-你是说 那小孩有武器  -是的 0.22口径的手枪

633
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:53,159
Same as did for his old man.
和杀了他爸爸口径一样的枪

634
00:41:53,160 --> 00:41:55,479
Don't worry, I took it off him, and then drove him home.
别担心 我从他那拿走了 把他送回家了

635
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:57,679
But while I was there, I found part of a metal canister
而且我在那里的时候 我还发现了一个金属小罐

636
00:41:57,680 --> 00:41:59,399
on the verge by where the taxi was parked.
就在出租车停着的地方边上

637
00:41:59,400 --> 00:42:01,279
-What sort of canister?  -I couldn't say.
-什么样的罐子  -说不好

638
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:03,159
I'd intended to take it to this naturist camp,
我本来想带着它去天体营

639
00:42:03,160 --> 00:42:04,359
but with the boy on board...
但车上还有个小男孩

640
00:42:04,360 --> 00:42:06,079
Pass it to Forensics for prints,
把它交给鉴证科 查查指纹

641
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:08,560
along with the pistol for comparison testing.
还有手枪 也去做对比测试

642
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:22,039
-Do you want to come down?  -No, you're all right.
-麻烦你下来一下吧  -不了吧

643
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:24,199
Mrs Walsh said it would be all right to carry on.
Walsh夫人说可以继续干

644
00:42:24,200 --> 00:42:25,639
Well, I'm saying it's not.
我说可不行

645
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:28,359
So, if you don't get down here and give your details to my sergeant,
所以 你要是不从梯子上下来 不把详细情况跟我的警长讲清楚

646
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,959
you'll have my foot up your arse!
我可要给你点颜色看看

647
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:32,159
Come on, Pops, don't be uptight. I've got a rota.
警长们 别这样 别这么暴躁嘛 我有一堆活要干呢

648
00:42:32,160 --> 00:42:33,959
If I don't do them now, it'll put me all out.
如果我现在不干的话 不会有好果子吃的

649
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:36,479
I'll put you all out if you don't get down that ladder!
你不从梯子上下来的话 我现在就不会给你好果子吃

650
00:42:36,480 --> 00:42:38,400
All right, all right, keep your hair on.
好吧好吧 别激动

651
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:44,799
Blimey, what's the matter with him? Ain't he getting any?
妈呀 他怎么回事 怎么脾气这么大

652
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:47,479
-Name, address and date of birth, please.  -Lee Timothy.
-请报一下姓名 住址 出生年月  -Lee Timothy

653
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:50,119
3 The Sidings, Jericho.
住在Jericho The Sidings 3号

654
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:52,479
12th October, 1950.
1950年10月12日生

655
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:54,799
When was the last time you saw Father Mahoney?
你最后一次见Mahoney神父是什么时候

656
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:57,599
Six weeks. The last time I did his windows.
六周前 上次我替他擦窗户的时候

657
00:42:57,600 --> 00:43:00,639
Did he ever mention any trouble he was having?
他有提到过他遇上了什么麻烦吗

658
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:02,519
Any difficulties with his parishioners?
和他的教区居民有什么过节吗

659
00:43:02,520 --> 00:43:04,239
To his window cleaner?
对他的窗户清理工讲吗

660
00:43:04,240 --> 00:43:05,680
No.
没有

661
00:43:06,880 --> 00:43:08,479
Right.
行吧

662
00:43:08,480 --> 00:43:10,719
Funny enough...
但有件事很有意思啊

663
00:43:10,720 --> 00:43:13,239
..I did hear him have a bit of a ding-dong last I was here.
上次我在这儿的时候确实听到他和别人发生点口角

664
00:43:13,240 --> 00:43:15,279
I was aloft doing the window.
我那时在擦窗户

665
00:43:15,280 --> 00:43:17,799
He was having a right old go at someone in the front bedroom.
他在前边的卧室冲某个人发火

666
00:43:17,800 --> 00:43:18,880
The top bay.
顶楼凸出的那个房间

667
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:22,839
Did you hear what he was saying, or see who he was talking to?
你听见他讲什么了吗 或是看见他在和谁说话吗

668
00:43:22,840 --> 00:43:25,199
No, not who was with him, but...
没有 没看到是谁 但是

669
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:27,719
..I saw a trilby on the hall table.
我看到大厅桌子上有顶毡帽

670
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:30,679
Little orange feather in the band. Too racy for the Father.
带子上有几根橙色羽毛 神父可不戴这么活泼的

671
00:43:30,680 --> 00:43:33,359
-What time was this?  -Early doors.
-那是什么时间  -早上挺早的

672
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:35,959
Right, I think that will be all for now, Mr Timothy, thank you.
好 现在应该没什么问题了 Timothy先生 谢谢你

673
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:37,799
If we need anything else, we'll be in touch.
如果我们还需要什么的话 会联系你的

674
00:43:37,800 --> 00:43:39,640
His ministry had taken him all over.
他做牧师的时候浪迹四方

675
00:43:40,680 --> 00:43:42,879
He'd been a padre in the war, I think.
我记得 他好像去当过战时牧师

676
00:43:42,880 --> 00:43:44,520
And a prison chaplain, too.
还当过监狱牧师

677
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:47,879
Did he have any family that you know of?
你知道他有什么家人吗

678
00:43:47,880 --> 00:43:50,679
He had a half-brother come by from time to time.
他有个继兄会时不时过来

679
00:43:50,680 --> 00:43:52,200
Donal.
叫Donal

680
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:55,720
But things weren't all that good between them.
但他们关系并不太好

681
00:43:56,880 --> 00:43:57,959
No?
关系不好

682
00:43:57,960 --> 00:43:59,599
How's that?
为什么

683
00:43:59,600 --> 00:44:01,680
He turned up every few months...
他隔几个月就会来一次

684
00:44:02,720 --> 00:44:04,679
..like the proverbial bad penny.
像狗皮膏药一样甩都甩不掉

685
00:44:04,680 --> 00:44:06,439
After money from the Father.
找神父要钱

686
00:44:06,440 --> 00:44:09,080
I told him I thought he was taking advantage.
我跟他说过 我觉得他就是赖上他了

687
00:44:10,040 --> 00:44:11,520
The Father said...
神父说

688
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:15,520
.."Am I not my brother's keeper, Roisin?"
我不就是我弟弟的监护人吗 Roisin

689
00:44:17,520 --> 00:44:19,320
"Am I not my brother's keeper?"
我不就是我弟弟的监护人吗

690
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:31,560
-Afternoon, Mrs Appleby.  -Afternoon.
-下午好 Appleby太太  -下午好

691
00:44:36,880 --> 00:44:37,959
Baz!
Baz

692
00:44:37,960 --> 00:44:39,519
Where the hell have you been?
你死哪去了

693
00:44:39,520 --> 00:44:41,999
-I've been going out of my mind.  -It's not a big deal.
-我都快急疯了  -没什么大事

694
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:43,599
I just had to get away.
我只是得离开一下

695
00:44:43,600 --> 00:44:45,959
-From me?  -No, from here.
-离开我吗  -不是 是离开这里

696
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:48,919
-It was just for an hour or two.  -Baz, you've been gone all night.
-就一两个小时  -Baz 你出去了一整晚

697
00:44:48,920 --> 00:44:50,519
Where did you go?
你去哪了

698
00:44:50,520 --> 00:44:52,240
A pub in town.
镇上的一家酒吧

699
00:44:53,440 --> 00:44:55,280
An old haunt from when I was an undergrad.
我读大学的时候常去

700
00:44:56,680 --> 00:44:59,880
I had too much to drink and passed out on Christchurch Meadow.
我喝多了 在基督教堂的草坪上醉倒了

701
00:45:03,840 --> 00:45:05,399
But I'm back now.
但我这不是回来了吗

702
00:45:05,400 --> 00:45:07,760
-I'll try and make a go of it.  -You don't have to.
-我会再努力试试看的  -不必勉强

703
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:11,239
-You can just go.  -No, I'd like to.
-想走就走吧  -不 我愿意

704
00:45:11,240 --> 00:45:12,879
Really.
真的

705
00:45:12,880 --> 00:45:14,840
I'll get over my hang-ups and...
我会克服自己的抵触心理 再说了

706
00:45:16,080 --> 00:45:17,639
..we've paid for the week.
我们付了一周的钱呢

707
00:45:17,640 --> 00:45:19,879
Let's just try and enjoy it.
不如试着好好享受吧

708
00:45:19,880 --> 00:45:20,960
Yes?
好吗

709
00:45:53,800 --> 00:45:56,159
-Anything from lippy?  -No, nothing much.
-小贫嘴那儿有什么收获吗  -没有 没什么重大突破

710
00:45:56,160 --> 00:45:59,119
Oh, other than he overheard Mahoney arguing with someone in his bedroom
哦 除了他上次来的时候无意中听见

711
00:45:59,120 --> 00:46:00,359
the last time he was here.
Mahoney在卧室里跟人争吵

712
00:46:00,360 --> 00:46:03,039
-Man or woman?  -He couldn't say.
-男的女的  -他说不准

713
00:46:03,040 --> 00:46:06,359
Though he did see a trilby through the window with an orange feather.
不过他透过窗户看到了一顶带橘色羽毛的软毡帽

714
00:46:06,360 --> 00:46:08,279
Not Mahoney's. So, presumably, a man.
那不是Mahoney的 所以 应该是个男的

715
00:46:08,280 --> 00:46:10,160
Could be his half-brother Donal.
可能是他同父异母的弟弟 Donal

716
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:13,759
Well, there's a...
这儿倒是写了个

717
00:46:13,760 --> 00:46:16,719
There's a "call D" in his diary.
他日程簿里写了个 打电话给D

718
00:46:16,720 --> 00:46:18,479
And his last appointment is confession.
而且他最后一场预约确实是做忏悔

719
00:46:18,480 --> 00:46:20,279
8:00pm. Ringed and underlined.
晚八点 圈起来还打了横线

720
00:46:20,280 --> 00:46:22,559
Kept by his killer, presumably.
来赴约的应该就是杀他的凶手

721
00:46:22,560 --> 00:46:23,920
Mm.
嗯

722
00:46:42,400 --> 00:46:44,599
The fruit of my labour.
我的劳动成果

723
00:46:44,600 --> 00:46:49,359
22, the same calibre as did for Mr Lunn.
0.22英寸 跟杀死Lunn先生的子弹口径相同

724
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:52,959
By your leave, I'll pass it to Forensic Ballistics for comparison.
你们不介意的话 我就把它送去法医弹道专家那做比对了

725
00:46:52,960 --> 00:46:54,359
See if we have a match.
看看是否一致

726
00:46:54,360 --> 00:46:56,999
Well, I can't imagine we've too many robbers going round Oxford
我想我们应该没那么多

727
00:46:57,000 --> 00:46:58,960
knocking people off with a .22 pistol.
带着把22口径手枪在牛津到处伤人的抢劫犯

728
00:47:03,720 --> 00:47:04,799
Three feathers.
三根羽毛

729
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:06,759
That was on Lunn's membership card, wasn't it?
Lunn的会员卡上也有这个吧

730
00:47:06,760 --> 00:47:08,599
Mm, The Fanciers' Club.
嗯 鸵鸟爱好者俱乐部

731
00:47:08,600 --> 00:47:11,839
"From the boys on D wing, Wandsworth."
旺兹沃斯监狱D翼楼的弟兄们赠

732
00:47:11,840 --> 00:47:15,039
His housekeeper said he was a prison chaplain.
他的管家说他以前做过监狱神父

733
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:17,399
It's a funny robbery that leaves a pocket watch.
抢劫犯放着怀表不要 挺奇怪的

734
00:47:17,400 --> 00:47:19,679
And it's smashed again.
这只也摔坏了

735
00:47:19,680 --> 00:47:21,999
Two broken timepieces?
两块表都坏了

736
00:47:22,000 --> 00:47:24,039
The killer's motif, perhaps?
会不会是凶手杀人的固定模式

737
00:47:24,040 --> 00:47:26,159
Do you still think it was just a robbery?
你还觉得这只是一起抢劫案吗

738
00:47:26,160 --> 00:47:27,719
3:50...
三点五十

739
00:47:27,720 --> 00:47:29,119
So, what's he after?
那他这么做图什么呢

740
00:47:29,120 --> 00:47:31,879
Trying to fix a false time to give himself an alibi, maybe?
会不会是想让我们搞错死亡时间 好让他有不在场证明

741
00:47:31,880 --> 00:47:34,040
Well, if that's his purpose, it's pretty redundant.
如果是为了这个目的 多此一举啊

742
00:47:35,720 --> 00:47:38,159
We know from Doctor DeBryn and from his appointment book
DeBryn医生还有他的预约登记簿都能告诉我们

743
00:47:38,160 --> 00:47:39,799
that Father Mahoney was shot at 8:00.
Mahoney神父是在八点遭遇枪击

744
00:47:39,800 --> 00:47:42,999
Well, whatever it means, I'd better get back and brief Mr Bright.
不论这意味着什么 我还是先回去汇报给Bright先生吧

745
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:45,839
Two deaths in as many days isn't gonna go down well at Division.
两天死俩 分局那边的人听了肯定笑不出来

746
00:47:45,840 --> 00:47:47,439
You can bank on it.
你就等着瞧吧

747
00:47:47,440 --> 00:47:50,319
I'll get back to the rectory, see if there's anything that this fits.
我回神父住所看看有没有适合佩戴这只怀表的衣服

748
00:47:50,320 --> 00:47:52,479
There was a wardrobe that I couldn't get into.
那儿有个衣柜我打不开

749
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:54,640
Just to make sure nothing's been overlooked.
我去确认一下有没有遗漏什么

750
00:49:06,960 --> 00:49:11,039
A taxi driver, and now a priest.
先是出租车司机 现在又死了个神父

751
00:49:11,040 --> 00:49:12,799
Anything to connect them?
他们之间有关联吗

752
00:49:12,800 --> 00:49:17,159
We've no reason to believe the dead men were known to each other, sir.
没有证据表明两名死者互相认识 长官

753
00:49:17,160 --> 00:49:20,119
Well, whoever's behind it, you need to find them, Thursday, and fast.
不论幕后凶手是谁 你得抓住他们 Thursday 要快

754
00:49:20,120 --> 00:49:22,519
I've already had Division on.
我已经给分局安排下去了

755
00:49:22,520 --> 00:49:26,560
If this is some lunatic murdering strangers at random for money...
如果这是个随机挑陌生人谋财害命的疯子

756
00:49:27,800 --> 00:49:30,439
..he's got 130,000 potential victims to choose from,
他有13万名潜在受害者可以随便挑

757
00:49:30,440 --> 00:49:32,520
and we've no way of knowing who's going to be next.
我们根本无法预知谁会是下一个

758
00:50:37,720 --> 00:50:39,679
Can't you wear a bell around your neck?
你不能在脖子上挂个铃铛吗

759
00:50:39,680 --> 00:50:42,039
Sorry. I've always been light of foot.
抱歉 我脚步一向很轻

760
00:50:42,040 --> 00:50:44,559
What are you doing skulking in there?
你躲里面干嘛呢

761
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:47,319
-Looking for absolution?  -It's too late for me.
-寻求宽恕吗  -对我来说太迟了

762
00:50:47,320 --> 00:50:48,399
I'm past saving.
我已经无可救药了

763
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:50,519
It's never too late for the Almighty.
在上帝眼中 什么时候都不算晚

764
00:50:50,520 --> 00:50:52,519
"Though your sins be as scarlet..."
你们的罪虽像硃红

765
00:50:52,520 --> 00:50:54,640
Did you know him? What was he like?
你认识他吗 他是个什么样的人

766
00:50:55,920 --> 00:50:57,839
Whisky priest.
他没表面上那么庄严

767
00:50:57,840 --> 00:51:00,079
They get that look sometimes, clergy. That...
他们神职人员有时会露出那种神情 那种

768
00:51:00,080 --> 00:51:03,959
..over-the-shoulder hunted cast to the eye,
一边逃命一边回头看的惊恐眼神

769
00:51:03,960 --> 00:51:06,359
as if they'll be discovered in their doubt.
像是怕被人发现他们信仰不够坚定一样

770
00:51:06,360 --> 00:51:08,079
You mean, he lost his faith?
你是说 他迷失了信仰

771
00:51:08,080 --> 00:51:09,720
Well, there's a lot of it about.
这在这一带挺常见的

772
00:51:13,600 --> 00:51:15,759
Have you ever heard of The Ostrich Fanciers' Club?
你听说过鸵鸟爱好者俱乐部吗

773
00:51:15,760 --> 00:51:17,519
No, that's new to me.
没有 第一次听说

774
00:51:17,520 --> 00:51:19,279
-Where is it?  -I don't know.
-在哪  -不知道

775
00:51:19,280 --> 00:51:22,480
-I'm not even sure what kind of club it is.  -I can ask around.
-我都不清楚它到底是个什么俱乐部  -我可以打听打听

776
00:51:31,200 --> 00:51:33,279
Aye-aye, what's this, then?
嚯 这儿干嘛呢

777
00:51:33,280 --> 00:51:34,919
A magic lantern show?
看幻灯片呢

778
00:51:34,920 --> 00:51:36,480
In a manner of speaking.
算是吧

779
00:51:38,120 --> 00:51:40,880
Oh! Blimey!
哦 天哪

780
00:51:41,880 --> 00:51:44,919
Morse found a bunch of them in a wardrobe up at the rectory.
Morse在神父住所的一个衣柜里找到了一堆这玩意儿

781
00:51:44,920 --> 00:51:46,599
All right, Morse.
行了 Morse

782
00:51:46,600 --> 00:51:48,639
We get the general idea.
我们大概清楚怎么回事了

783
00:51:50,680 --> 00:51:52,319
Pornography?
色情片

784
00:51:52,320 --> 00:51:54,639
That's not Oxford business. That's London business.
牛津不兴这个啊 伦敦才有吧

785
00:51:54,640 --> 00:51:57,560
An hour's run up the A40 makes it everybody's business.
开车走A40高速公路就一小时车程 谁都别想好

786
00:51:58,680 --> 00:52:00,599
I've got an old colleague in the Dirty Squad.
我在下流犯罪小队有个老同事

787
00:52:00,600 --> 00:52:02,040
I'll see if he can shed any light.
我可以让他帮忙看看

788
00:52:03,280 --> 00:52:06,079
Well, it wasn't Father Mahoney at the station cafe.
去车站咖啡馆的不是Mahoney神父

789
00:52:06,080 --> 00:52:08,879
I showed his photo to the waitress. She said it was another fella.
我给服务员看了他的照片 她说是别人

790
00:52:08,880 --> 00:52:11,039
Hello, hello, that's, er...
咦 那是

791
00:52:11,040 --> 00:52:12,879
-..a Masonic apron.  -Yeah, we know.
-共济会的围裙  -没错 我们知道

792
00:52:12,880 --> 00:52:14,639
It was with the blue films in the bag.
它和那些黄片一起装在包里

793
00:52:14,640 --> 00:52:17,319
Well, it couldn't have been Father Mahoney's. The Pope stuck a ban
它不可能是Mahoney神父的 教皇约200年前就明令禁止

794
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:19,679
on Romans joining the Brotherhood nearly 200 years back.
天主教徒加入共济会

795
00:52:19,680 --> 00:52:21,799
His brother Donal, maybe.
可能是他弟弟Donal的

796
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:24,200
-He sounds like a wrong 'un.  -Sir...
-他听着就不是什么好东西  -长官

797
00:52:26,240 --> 00:52:27,560
These canisters...
这些罐头

798
00:52:28,600 --> 00:52:30,240
A tin can, you say?
你说锡制罐头

799
00:52:31,560 --> 00:52:34,159
Well, you find all sorts in hedgerows.
树篱里什么都有嘛

800
00:52:34,160 --> 00:52:36,279
No, it was half a canister.
不 是半个罐头

801
00:52:36,280 --> 00:52:38,799
It may have contained eight millimetre film stock.
里面可能装过8毫米的胶片

802
00:52:38,800 --> 00:52:41,719
Well, we have a film show once a week for the guests.
我们每周都会为客人们安排一场电影

803
00:52:41,720 --> 00:52:45,320
We've a small library of them, but they're all 16 mil.
我们收藏了一些影片 但都是16毫米的

804
00:52:46,560 --> 00:52:50,039
The couple that heard the shot, Major, Mr and Mrs Appleby,
听见枪响的那对夫妻 少校 Appleby夫妇

805
00:52:50,040 --> 00:52:52,519
-when did they arrive?  -Friday evening.
-他们什么时候到的  -周五晚上

806
00:52:52,520 --> 00:52:55,199
We gave them their flower garlands by way of a welcome.
我们为他们戴上了花环作为欢迎

807
00:52:55,200 --> 00:52:56,719
I asked if they wanted to dine,
我问过他们要不要用餐

808
00:52:56,720 --> 00:52:59,639
but they were very tired and wanted to get straight to bed.
但他们都很疲惫 想直接去睡觉

809
00:52:59,640 --> 00:53:01,559
We didn't see them again till morning.
我们直到早上才再次见到他们

810
00:53:01,560 --> 00:53:04,519
We were going to drive up, but then we thought,
我们本来打算开车来的 但后来我们想着

811
00:53:04,520 --> 00:53:07,159
if we really are going to get back to nature
如果我们真想回归自然

812
00:53:07,160 --> 00:53:09,639
we ought to take the train and get a cab.
我们就该先坐火车 再打个车

813
00:53:09,640 --> 00:53:12,039
And can you describe the driver?
还记得那位司机什么样吗

814
00:53:12,040 --> 00:53:13,639
-The driver?  -Mm-hm.
-司机  -嗯

815
00:53:13,640 --> 00:53:15,279
Oh, yes.
哦 记得

816
00:53:15,280 --> 00:53:16,919
You lied to us.
你对我们撒谎了

817
00:53:16,920 --> 00:53:18,119
Turns out you were the one
原来你才是

818
00:53:18,120 --> 00:53:20,159
who dropped the Applebys at Paradise Court
谋杀当晚

819
00:53:20,160 --> 00:53:21,960
the same night as the murder.
送Appleby夫妇到天堂院的人

820
00:53:23,040 --> 00:53:26,920
I can see I should have mentioned it, but I've had a lot on my mind.
现在想来我确实应该提一下 但我忙昏头了

821
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:29,959
My wife's been sick, sir.
我妻子病了 警官

822
00:53:29,960 --> 00:53:32,439
-Back and forth to the doctor.  -I'm sorry to hear it.
-反反复复看医生  -我很遗憾

823
00:53:32,440 --> 00:53:34,040
And where were you last night?
你昨晚在哪

824
00:53:35,160 --> 00:53:37,239
Well, now, sir, you know where I was.
我说 警官 您知道我在哪啊

825
00:53:37,240 --> 00:53:39,239
I had a little accident with the officer.
我跟这位警官出了点小事故

826
00:53:39,240 --> 00:53:42,480
But I made sure he was all right and took him home.
但我确认了他没事 还送他回了家

827
00:53:43,800 --> 00:53:45,440
Before that.
在那之前呢

828
00:53:46,480 --> 00:53:48,279
Oh...
哦

829
00:53:48,280 --> 00:53:50,439
I had fares all over.
到处接送乘客啊

830
00:53:50,440 --> 00:53:51,880
Anything take you near St Agnes?
有去St Agnes附近的单子吗

831
00:53:53,360 --> 00:53:55,360
No, sir, I don't believe it did.
没有 警官 我不记得到过那边

832
00:53:56,720 --> 00:53:59,319
And was everything all right between you and Mr Lunn?
你和Lunn先生关系还好吗

833
00:53:59,320 --> 00:54:01,439
-Me and Dudley?  -Yeah.
-我和Dudley  -对

834
00:54:01,440 --> 00:54:04,280
Yeah, sure, we was good friends, you know.
当然好啊 我们可是好哥们儿

835
00:54:05,880 --> 00:54:09,919
-Ask any of the men on the rank.  -No money worries or anything?
-随便找个同行问问  -没有金钱之类的纠纷吗

836
00:54:09,920 --> 00:54:13,239
It's just I found this marker in the back of your cab last night.
只是我昨晚在你车后座上找到了这张借条

837
00:54:13,240 --> 00:54:16,799
It's an IOU for £25 on the back of a Speedy Cabs card
25镑的欠条 写在了极速出租车名片的背面

838
00:54:16,800 --> 00:54:18,879
and signed by Mr Lunn.
上面有Lunn先生的签名

839
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:21,199
Oh, now, see, sir, that...
哦 这个嘛 警官 那个

840
00:54:21,200 --> 00:54:23,880
That was just a little private matter between us.
那只是我们之间一件小小的私事

841
00:54:25,000 --> 00:54:27,719
Besides, Dudley paid all of that back a long time ago.
况且 Dudley早就还清了

842
00:54:27,720 --> 00:54:30,399
In my experience, Mr Haynes, when a debt is paid,
以我的经验 Haynes先生 欠的钱要是还清了

843
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:32,159
the marker's returned to the debtor.
借条会还给借款人

844
00:54:32,160 --> 00:54:33,759
Else destroyed.
或者销毁

845
00:54:33,760 --> 00:54:35,479
Also, £25, what's that?
另外 25镑 这是多少

846
00:54:35,480 --> 00:54:37,359
A week's wages or more.
一周的薪水 可能还不止

847
00:54:37,360 --> 00:54:38,919
Well, sir...
我说 警官

848
00:54:38,920 --> 00:54:42,119
..we all puts a little bit by for a rainy day, don't we?
我们都会存点钱以备不时之需的吧

849
00:54:42,120 --> 00:54:45,919
But you can see why we're finding it difficult to believe
但是相信你也清楚 我们很难相信

850
00:54:45,920 --> 00:54:48,279
that you being out at Paradise Court
欠了你钱的受害者被枪杀的那晚

851
00:54:48,280 --> 00:54:51,479
on the same night that a man, who owes you money, is shot dead
你明明去了天堂院

852
00:54:51,480 --> 00:54:53,479
is something that might just slip your mind.
却说自己忘记了这件事

853
00:54:53,480 --> 00:54:54,679
Look...
好吧

854
00:54:54,680 --> 00:54:56,640
Maybe I should've said something.
或许我是该说些什么

855
00:54:57,640 --> 00:55:00,079
But I didn't want to get involved in that kind of trouble.
但我不想卷入这些麻烦之中

856
00:55:00,080 --> 00:55:02,040
Murder trouble, you know.
谋杀案 你懂的

857
00:55:03,320 --> 00:55:05,120
I'm just a taxi driver.
我只是个出租车司机

858
00:55:06,320 --> 00:55:08,680
I mind my business.
我只管接送乘客

859
00:55:14,760 --> 00:55:16,519
Mr and Mrs Maynard?
Maynard先生 太太

860
00:55:16,520 --> 00:55:18,559
-Good afternoon.  -Good afternoon.
-下午好  -下午好

861
00:55:18,560 --> 00:55:20,119
Thank you.
谢谢

862
00:55:20,120 --> 00:55:21,719
Farewell, my dear.
再见 亲爱的

863
00:55:21,720 --> 00:55:23,399
-Have a lovely trip.  -Thank you.
-旅途愉快  -谢谢

864
00:55:23,400 --> 00:55:26,080
-See you in a few days, darling.  -I'll get the door.
-回见 亲爱的  -我来开门

865
00:55:29,560 --> 00:55:30,960
And here's your coat.
外套给你

866
00:55:34,400 --> 00:55:35,679
Thank you.
谢了

867
00:55:35,680 --> 00:55:37,240
-Drive safely.  -Will do.
-注意安全  -放心吧

868
00:55:40,720 --> 00:55:43,039
Right, to the station, then.
好 那就去车站了

869
00:56:03,640 --> 00:56:07,599
Well, if this is what you get up to living here by yourself,
好嘛 如果你一个住在这里就是干这些

870
00:56:07,600 --> 00:56:10,999
no wonder you can't get a decent girl to look at you.
难怪没有正经女孩看得上你

871
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:12,599
It's evidence.
这是证据

872
00:56:12,600 --> 00:56:14,520
In a murder case.
谋杀案的

873
00:56:18,320 --> 00:56:21,800
There's more to the world than you find in Reveille, Gwen.
坐井观天 曰天小者 非天小也 Gwen

874
00:56:22,920 --> 00:56:25,599
And you'd know all about it, I'm sure.
确实 你什么都懂

875
00:56:25,600 --> 00:56:27,520
Because you went to Oxford.
毕竟你考上了牛津

876
00:56:29,080 --> 00:56:31,599
But you didn't finish it, though, did you?
却没读完 不是吗

877
00:56:31,600 --> 00:56:34,959
For all your books and your poetry...
就为了你那些书啊诗的

878
00:56:34,960 --> 00:56:37,080
..and your snooty music...
还有高雅音乐

879
00:56:38,680 --> 00:56:40,599
-..you failed.  -Yep!
-辍学了  -没错

880
00:56:40,600 --> 00:56:41,680
Yep, I failed.
没错 我辍学了

881
00:56:42,760 --> 00:56:45,359
I should have stayed at home and...
我就应该呆在家里

882
00:56:45,360 --> 00:56:47,120
..drove a taxi, like my father.
开辆出租车 像我爸一样

883
00:56:48,120 --> 00:56:50,319
And then got one of the local girls knocked up.
然后把一个当地女孩的肚子搞大

884
00:56:50,320 --> 00:56:53,519
Then you could look down your nose at me, and all would be well
这样你就可以对我颐指气使 在你的方寸世界里

885
00:56:53,520 --> 00:56:55,920
in your tiny, little world.
一切都是如此完美

886
00:56:58,480 --> 00:57:01,439
You were always a strange one.
你从来就是个怪咖

887
00:57:01,440 --> 00:57:03,759
Close and private.
离群自闭

888
00:57:03,760 --> 00:57:06,480
Filled with your sweaty, little secrets.
满脑子都是见不得人的小秘密

889
00:57:07,720 --> 00:57:10,959
-You were a disappointment to him.  -So you said.
-你真是令他失望  -你说的对

890
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:13,359
A big disappointment. So you said.
-失望至极  -你说的对

891
00:57:13,360 --> 00:57:15,240
I didn't kill her!
我没有害死她

892
00:57:17,480 --> 00:57:18,840
What?
什么

893
00:57:20,840 --> 00:57:22,600
I didn't give her cancer.
我没有让她得癌症

894
00:57:23,800 --> 00:57:27,200
And you can't blame me all your life.
你不能一辈子都怪在我头上

895
00:57:39,160 --> 00:57:40,560
I've got work to do.
我还有工作要做

896
00:57:41,920 --> 00:57:43,280
Goodnight, Gwen.
晚安 Gwen

897
00:57:49,400 --> 00:57:51,240
We took you in.
是我们收留了你

898
00:58:19,080 --> 00:58:20,799
It's Lunn? You're sure?
那是Lunn 你确定

899
00:58:20,800 --> 00:58:23,479
It's definitely him. He's in two or three of the pictures.
肯定是他 有两三张图里都有他

900
00:58:23,480 --> 00:58:25,319
That's his connection to Father Mahoney.
这是他和Mahoney神父之间的联系

901
00:58:25,320 --> 00:58:27,760
Lunn's a performer in these blue films, which...
Lunn是这些色情片的演员之一 这些片子

902
00:58:29,200 --> 00:58:31,279
There's no need to clam up on my account.
你们不必在我这里有什么忌讳

903
00:58:31,280 --> 00:58:33,479
Oh, I'll get it.
噢 我去接

904
00:58:33,480 --> 00:58:37,600
I was in Blackpool with the ATS for two years during the war.
二战期间 我和ATS一起在Blackpool

905
00:58:38,520 --> 00:58:39,639
And there was this man
就是这个男人

906
00:58:39,640 --> 00:58:42,199
and he kept asking me if he could measure my feet.
他一直问能不能量量我脚的尺寸

907
00:58:42,200 --> 00:58:45,039
I know, it takes all sorts, but...
我知道 这需要很多因缘际会 但

908
00:58:45,040 --> 00:58:46,400
..there we go.
我们走到了今天

909
00:58:48,280 --> 00:58:49,600
You're looking tired.
你看起来很疲惫

910
00:58:50,560 --> 00:58:52,040
It's work.
工作如此

911
00:58:54,160 --> 00:58:55,920
You must look after yourself.
你一定要照顾好自己

912
00:58:57,680 --> 00:58:59,560
We all think a lot of you, you know?
我们都很挂念你 你知道吗

913
00:59:01,880 --> 00:59:04,040
I'm sorry you've had a bad go.
我很抱歉 你有过一些糟糕的经历

914
00:59:05,960 --> 00:59:07,920
-Right.  -Well...
-好了  -那么

915
00:59:09,080 --> 00:59:11,479
Come home safe, Dad.
平安回来 孩子他爸

916
00:59:11,480 --> 00:59:12,600
Morse.
Morse

917
00:59:13,840 --> 00:59:15,440
That was the factory.
那是一个制片基地

918
00:59:45,360 --> 00:59:48,719
He's the Worshipful Master at my lodge.
他是我们共济会会所的会长

919
00:59:48,720 --> 00:59:51,000
Commodore Maynard. Harry Maynard.
Maynard准将 Harry Maynard

920
00:59:52,280 --> 00:59:55,239
I only saw him the night before last at the, er...
我只在前天晚上见过他

921
00:59:55,240 --> 00:59:56,879
..the lodge.
在会所里

922
00:59:56,880 --> 00:59:58,319
Who found him?
谁发现他的

923
00:59:58,320 --> 00:59:59,799
A beat constable.
一个巡警

924
00:59:59,800 --> 01:00:01,359
Anonymous tip-off.
匿名报警

925
01:00:01,360 --> 01:00:03,239
Next door thought they heard a pistol crack
隔壁的人觉得在昨晚九点左右

926
01:00:03,240 --> 01:00:05,039
about nine o'clock last night.
听到了手枪声

927
01:00:05,040 --> 01:00:06,840
That would chime with the grandfather.
这和老古董的说法相吻合

928
01:00:08,680 --> 01:00:10,799
-Morning, gentlemen.  -Doctor.
-早上好 先生们  -法医

929
01:00:10,800 --> 01:00:12,439
Oh, yes.
噢 是的

930
01:00:12,440 --> 01:00:14,039
That does look nasty.
看起来挺糟糕

931
01:00:14,040 --> 01:00:18,079
You seem to be making a habit of collecting these, Chief Inspector.
看来你是要集齐这一类的案件了 总督察

932
01:00:18,080 --> 01:00:19,519
Shot?
枪杀

933
01:00:19,520 --> 01:00:22,919
In the back of the head at point-blank range
近距离击中后脑勺

934
01:00:22,920 --> 01:00:25,239
would be my first impression.
我的第一判断

935
01:00:25,240 --> 01:00:26,919
Three in as many days.
这几天的第三起了

936
01:00:26,920 --> 01:00:28,119
Oh...
噢

937
01:00:28,120 --> 01:00:31,400
And I think his wife has just arrived by taxi.
我想他的夫人应该刚下出租车

938
01:00:42,400 --> 01:00:43,919
Good heavens, it's...
天呐 这是

939
01:00:43,920 --> 01:00:45,959
Detective Sergeant Strange, Mrs Maynard.
我是Strange警长 Maynard太太

940
01:00:45,960 --> 01:00:47,920
If we could speak inside.
我们能去里面聊聊吗

941
01:00:52,840 --> 01:00:55,679
-Where have you come from?  -The station.
-你从哪里开过来的  -车站

942
01:00:55,680 --> 01:00:58,239
I picked her up from here and dropped her there last night.
我昨晚从这里接的她 然后把她送到那儿的

943
01:00:58,240 --> 01:01:00,879
-What time was this?  -Er, 5:45.
-是在什么时间  -呃 5点45

944
01:01:00,880 --> 01:01:02,599
Something like that.
大概是这个时候

945
01:01:02,600 --> 01:01:05,160
She'd booked a return for 9:30 this morning.
她预约了一个今天早上九点半的返程

946
01:01:06,720 --> 01:01:08,879
Look, can I go now? I've got a pick up in Headington.
那么 我能走了吗 我还得去Headington接客

947
01:01:08,880 --> 01:01:10,919
Brian's not turned in and Ifan's doing his nut.
Brian还没有回来 Ifan也没有空

948
01:01:10,920 --> 01:01:13,279
No, I'd like you to give this officer a formal statement
不行 我需要你向这位警官做一个陈述

949
01:01:13,280 --> 01:01:14,959
and then you can leave.
然后才可以走

950
01:01:14,960 --> 01:01:17,079
Go on.
去吧

951
01:01:17,080 --> 01:01:18,799
Are you OK?
还好吗

952
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:20,840
-Three shootings in a week?  -Shh...
-一周内的第三起枪杀案  -嘘

953
01:01:22,040 --> 01:01:24,319
-Here...  -What's this?
-给  -这是什么

954
01:01:24,320 --> 01:01:25,839
It's your Ostrich Fanciers' Club.
这是你的鸵鸟爱好者俱乐部

955
01:01:25,840 --> 01:01:28,399
One of the classified ads boys recognised the name.
一个负责广告分类的男孩认出了这个名字

956
01:01:28,400 --> 01:01:31,199
"The glamour of exotic rare birds."
"异域珍禽的魅力所在"

957
01:01:31,200 --> 01:01:32,839
"Films £1.
"胶片1镑

958
01:01:32,840 --> 01:01:37,559
"Send a stamped address envelope to The Ostrich Fanciers' Club,
"信封需贴2.5便士邮票 寄至 鸵鸟同好俱乐部

959
01:01:37,560 --> 01:01:40,200
"The Rectory, 12 Cloister Walk, Oxon."
"教区长宅邸 修道院步行街12号 牛津郡"

960
01:01:41,720 --> 01:01:43,280
Exotic rare birds?
异域珍禽

961
01:01:44,440 --> 01:01:46,959
For the one-in-the-hand brigade, I fancy,
我猜 是有些组织宁愿"一鸟在手"

962
01:01:46,960 --> 01:01:49,519
rather than the two-in-the-bush contingent.
也不愿放任"二鸟在林"

963
01:01:49,520 --> 01:01:50,879
Right.
是了

964
01:01:50,880 --> 01:01:52,559
Happy to be of personal service.
很高兴能帮到你

965
01:01:52,560 --> 01:01:53,960
Thank you.
谢了

966
01:02:38,520 --> 01:02:41,439
We understand he was involved in the Masonic Order.
我们得知他是共济会的一员

967
01:02:41,440 --> 01:02:43,239
Is that right?
是这样吗

968
01:02:43,240 --> 01:02:45,439
He was in charge of the lodge.
他在会所里管事

969
01:02:45,440 --> 01:02:48,359
We only had our ladies' night this week.
我们这周只去了那次女士晚宴

970
01:02:48,360 --> 01:02:50,279
He was so proud.
他很以此为傲

971
01:02:50,280 --> 01:02:51,799
Mrs Maynard...
Maynard太太

972
01:02:51,800 --> 01:02:54,879
..does The Ostrich Fanciers' Club mean anything to you?
鸵鸟爱好者俱乐部对你意味着什么吗

973
01:02:54,880 --> 01:02:56,559
No.
不

974
01:02:56,560 --> 01:02:58,400
Nothing at all. Should it?
并没有 该有吗

975
01:03:01,200 --> 01:03:03,039
Oh, now, that's a shame.
噢 真是可惜了

976
01:03:03,040 --> 01:03:04,760
The clock's broken, sir.
这个钟坏了 长官

977
01:03:05,840 --> 01:03:08,559
And it always kept such good time.
它一直都很准时

978
01:03:08,560 --> 01:03:11,040
Harry wouldn't have had it in the house otherwise.
不然Harry也不会一直把它放在家里

979
01:03:32,200 --> 01:03:33,879
Sir...
长官

980
01:03:33,880 --> 01:03:36,799
There are two indentations in the flower bed,
花坛里有两个压痕

981
01:03:36,800 --> 01:03:38,559
spaced about a foot apart.
间隔约一英尺

982
01:03:38,560 --> 01:03:40,599
I think I know who made the tip-off call.
我想我知道是谁匿名报警的了

983
01:03:40,600 --> 01:03:42,199
A ladder, you mean?
你是指 那个梯工

984
01:03:42,200 --> 01:03:44,719
Well, if Acacia Avenue is on Lee Timothy's round,
如果Acacia大道就在Lee Timothy的附近

985
01:03:44,720 --> 01:03:46,719
I can understand why he wouldn't want to be found
我可以理解为什么他不想在

986
01:03:46,720 --> 01:03:48,239
at the scene of a murder two days running.
连续两天的谋杀案现场被发现

987
01:03:48,240 --> 01:03:50,559
What's all that about Maynards carriage clock?
Maynard家的旅行钟是怎么回事

988
01:03:50,560 --> 01:03:53,399
Changing the time seems to be the killer's calling card.
更改时间似乎是这个凶手的特色

989
01:03:53,400 --> 01:03:54,919
Though, God knows why.
大概只有上帝知道吧

990
01:03:54,920 --> 01:03:56,800
-What do you think, Morse?  -I've...
-你怎么看 Morse  -我之前

991
01:03:58,280 --> 01:04:01,199
-I've seen this room before.  -What, been here, you mean?
-我之前见过这个房间  -什么 你是指 你来过这儿

992
01:04:01,200 --> 01:04:04,400
This is the room where Dudley Lunn's blue film was shot.
这间房间就是Dudley Lunn拍色情片的地方

993
01:04:09,480 --> 01:04:11,439
But you can see why I didn't want to get involved.
但你明白我为什么不想掺合进来

994
01:04:11,440 --> 01:04:12,599
Two people dead on the round
两天内有两个人死在了附近

995
01:04:12,600 --> 01:04:14,399
in two days could play havoc on my goodwill.
我的好意或许会给自己带来麻烦

996
01:04:14,400 --> 01:04:16,919
I'm Squeegee Lee, not Typhoid Mary!
我只是玻璃Lee 不是风暴Mary

997
01:04:16,920 --> 01:04:19,479
-How well did you know the Maynards?  -They're customers.
-你和Maynard一家熟吗  -就是普通客户

998
01:04:19,480 --> 01:04:22,240
I clean the windows, they pay me. That's it.
我清理窗户 他们付钱 就是这样

999
01:04:25,960 --> 01:04:27,879
And where were you last night at nine o'clock?
那你昨晚九点的时候在哪里

1000
01:04:27,880 --> 01:04:30,039
Meeting my bird, wasn't I?
见我女朋友 不行吗

1001
01:04:30,040 --> 01:04:31,759
She works of an evening part-time.
她晚上有兼职

1002
01:04:31,760 --> 01:04:33,999
Gets off about 10:00 and I walk her home.
10点左右结束 我陪她走回家

1003
01:04:34,000 --> 01:04:36,880
So, no-one can vouch for your movements last night at 9:00?
所以 没有人可以证明你昨晚九点的行踪了

1004
01:04:38,440 --> 01:04:42,160
Not when you put it like that. No.
如果你这么说的话 没有

1005
01:04:43,720 --> 01:04:45,440
Right.
好的

1006
01:05:25,200 --> 01:05:26,319
Morse.
Morse

1007
01:05:26,320 --> 01:05:27,559
Ah, Morse.
啊 Morse

1008
01:05:27,560 --> 01:05:29,919
I was hoping for a few words with DCI Thursday.
我想和Thursday总督察说几句话

1009
01:05:29,920 --> 01:05:31,919
He's gone to London, sir.
他去伦敦了 长官

1010
01:05:31,920 --> 01:05:34,319
Looking for a lead on this Ostrich Fanciers' Club.
去找鸵鸟爱好者俱乐部的领头人

1011
01:05:34,320 --> 01:05:36,799
We think Father Mahoney's step-brother,
我们觉得Mahoney神父的弟弟

1012
01:05:36,800 --> 01:05:38,399
Donal, might be involved.
Donal 可能和案子有关

1013
01:05:38,400 --> 01:05:41,479
This smutty films case, wretched business.
这些低俗的影片 肮脏的交易

1014
01:05:41,480 --> 01:05:44,039
Very well. Keep me apprised of any developments.
很好 有什么进展随时向我汇报

1015
01:05:44,040 --> 01:05:45,800
-Carry on.  -Sir.
-去吧  -是

1016
01:05:50,000 --> 01:05:51,319
Ah, matey, glad I caught you.
啊 伙计 正好遇上你

1017
01:05:51,320 --> 01:05:53,799
I've got this woman being knocked about by her husband.
有一位女士正受到丈夫的家暴

1018
01:05:53,800 --> 01:05:56,279
Uniform would like us to take a statement.
同事们想让我们去录口供

1019
01:05:56,280 --> 01:05:57,759
Can you deal?
你能来吗

1020
01:05:57,760 --> 01:05:59,999
Well, it's that or watching DeBryn
要不然你就看着DeBryn

1021
01:06:00,000 --> 01:06:02,399
rooting around Maynard's brain pan at the postmortem.
在验尸房翻查Maynard的头盖骨

1022
01:06:02,400 --> 01:06:03,920
I thought you'd sooner the frail.
你还不如选那位太太

1023
01:06:10,000 --> 01:06:11,479
I won't press charges.
我不会起诉的

1024
01:06:11,480 --> 01:06:13,279
It's my fault. I provoked him.
都是我的错 我惹恼了他

1025
01:06:13,280 --> 01:06:15,960
There's nothing you could have done that would warrant this.
无论你做了什么 他也不该这样对你

1026
01:06:16,920 --> 01:06:17,960
I met somebody.
我认识了别人

1027
01:06:19,480 --> 01:06:21,000
I went with him.
跟他交往了

1028
01:06:22,560 --> 01:06:24,280
And your husband found out?
被你丈夫发现了

1029
01:06:25,640 --> 01:06:28,199
And who was he, this other man?
那个男人是谁

1030
01:06:28,200 --> 01:06:31,680
-I don't want him getting in any trouble.  -Please, Mrs Grady.
-我不想让他惹上麻烦  -请说出来吧 Grady太太

1031
01:06:33,840 --> 01:06:35,239
It's Dudley.
是Dudley

1032
01:06:35,240 --> 01:06:36,639
Dudley Lunn.
Dudley Lunn

1033
01:06:41,320 --> 01:06:43,560
Where can I find your husband?
你丈夫现在在哪

1034
01:06:45,360 --> 01:06:47,239
He's at a place called Paradise Court.
他在一个叫天堂院的地方

1035
01:06:47,240 --> 01:06:49,079
But I don't want to press any charges.
但我不想起诉

1036
01:06:49,080 --> 01:06:50,759
Mrs Grady?
Grady太太

1037
01:06:50,760 --> 01:06:52,719
Joan Thursday, Welfare Officer.
我是Joan Thursday 社工

1038
01:06:52,720 --> 01:06:55,799
You don't have to talk to Detective Sergeant Morse if you don't want to.
你不想说的话可以不跟Morse探长说

1039
01:06:55,800 --> 01:06:57,639
I've told him I don't want to press charges.
我跟他说了我不想起诉

1040
01:06:57,640 --> 01:06:58,839
Please...
拜托了

1041
01:06:58,840 --> 01:07:01,160
Well, then, that should be enough.
好的 说这些就够了

1042
01:07:03,800 --> 01:07:05,160
Thank you, Officer.
谢谢 警官

1043
01:07:06,680 --> 01:07:09,920
Well, if you change your mind, you can find me at Castle Gate.
如果你改主意了 可以来城门警局找我

1044
01:08:08,720 --> 01:08:10,719
-Are you sure about Grady?  -I'm not sure, no.
-你确定是Grady吗  -我不确定

1045
01:08:10,720 --> 01:08:12,879
But it's a bit of a coincidence that his wife's lover
但他妻子的情夫在他工作地附近的乡间小道上

1046
01:08:12,880 --> 01:08:16,079
is killed on a country lane not far from where he works.
被杀害了 这也太巧了吧

1047
01:08:16,080 --> 01:08:18,799
Good evening. We're looking for your groundsman, Del Grady.
晚上好 我们在找你们的园丁 Del Grady

1048
01:08:18,800 --> 01:08:21,639
We've tried his home, to no avail.
我们去他家找过 但没找到

1049
01:08:49,280 --> 01:08:51,239
Some sort of Peeping Tom?
是偷窥狂吗

1050
01:08:51,240 --> 01:08:53,799
A groundsman at a naturist camp,
在天体营做园丁

1051
01:08:53,800 --> 01:08:55,199
it's hard to imagine a position
这种职位

1052
01:08:55,200 --> 01:08:57,440
that affords greater opportunity for voyeurism.
对于偷窥狂来说简直就是天时地利

1053
01:08:59,400 --> 01:09:01,599
Anything out of the ordinary, Doc?
有什么反常之处吗 法医

1054
01:09:01,600 --> 01:09:03,439
All too ordinary, I'm afraid.
恐怕是太正常了

1055
01:09:03,440 --> 01:09:06,199
The postmortem may say otherwise.
验尸结果也许会有反转

1056
01:09:06,200 --> 01:09:08,079
But at first glance,
但乍看之下

1057
01:09:08,080 --> 01:09:10,599
there's nothing to say it's other than it looks.
跟表面现象没什么相反之处

1058
01:09:10,600 --> 01:09:13,639
-Suicide.  -For the Coroner to decide, of course.
-自杀  -当然还需要验尸官确认

1059
01:09:13,640 --> 01:09:17,479
But there's a strong smell of liquor about the corpus.
不过尸体上有强烈的酒气

1060
01:09:17,480 --> 01:09:21,759
Alcohol taken to excess is a notorious depressant,
众所周知 过量饮酒会让人消沉

1061
01:09:21,760 --> 01:09:24,960
and we rarely make wise choices when inebriated.
喝醉的时候很难做出明智的选择

1062
01:09:27,400 --> 01:09:29,639
Anyway, er, shall we say nine of the clock?
晚上九点见吧

1063
01:09:29,640 --> 01:09:31,319
Mm-hm. Doctor.
好的 法医

1064
01:09:31,320 --> 01:09:32,600
Morse.
Morse

1065
01:09:36,360 --> 01:09:37,680
So...
所以

1066
01:09:39,240 --> 01:09:41,719
..he puts his wife in hospital...
他把妻子打进了医院

1067
01:09:41,720 --> 01:09:43,879
..then does for himself in a fit of remorse, then?
然后出于悔恨自杀了

1068
01:09:43,880 --> 01:09:45,279
Or it's what he did to Lunn
或者是他对Lunn等人

1069
01:09:45,280 --> 01:09:48,040
and the others that just pushed him over the edge.
犯下的罪行让他走上了极端

1070
01:09:49,400 --> 01:09:50,799
I can see Lunn,
看得出来他为什么杀Lunn

1071
01:09:50,800 --> 01:09:53,039
if he was carrying on with Mrs Grady.
如果他和Grady太太有染

1072
01:09:53,040 --> 01:09:56,119
But where's your motive for Father Mahoney and Commodore Maynard?
但是杀害Mahoney神父和Maynard准将的动机呢

1073
01:09:56,120 --> 01:09:59,319
They can't have been seeing her, too.
他们不可能也在和她交往

1074
01:09:59,320 --> 01:10:00,959
I'll get on for a search warrant.
我会去申请搜查令

1075
01:10:00,960 --> 01:10:03,079
But unless Grady has a .22 pistol at home,
但是除非Grady家里放着一把22口径手枪

1076
01:10:03,080 --> 01:10:05,400
we're gonna have to look elsewhere for a killer.
不然凶手就要从别处查起了

1077
01:10:54,280 --> 01:10:56,000
It was just a mistake.
只是个错误

1078
01:10:57,760 --> 01:10:59,840
A silly, youthful indiscretion.
年轻时傻傻的冲动

1079
01:11:02,360 --> 01:11:03,840
Did you meet him...
那天晚上

1080
01:11:04,920 --> 01:11:06,999
..the other night, down by the lane?
你在小路那边和他见面了吗

1081
01:11:07,000 --> 01:11:08,879
Only, my colleague found a paper flower
我同事在Lunn的出租车停靠的地方

1082
01:11:08,880 --> 01:11:10,599
out by where Lunn's taxi was parked.
发现了一片纸花

1083
01:11:10,600 --> 01:11:12,039
And I know that you and your wife
我知道你和你妻子

1084
01:11:12,040 --> 01:11:14,640
were given Hawaiian garlands the evening you arrived.
到这里的那天晚上收到了夏威夷花环

1085
01:11:16,880 --> 01:11:19,039
I just wanted to clear the air.
我只是想和他说清楚

1086
01:11:19,040 --> 01:11:22,999
To make plain that whatever youthful indiscretion had taken place
无论年轻时我们有过什么样的冲动

1087
01:11:23,000 --> 01:11:24,719
belonged in the past.
那都是过去式了

1088
01:11:24,720 --> 01:11:26,519
I'm a married man now.
我已经结婚了

1089
01:11:26,520 --> 01:11:28,359
-And so was Del.  -Well, he was.
-Del也是  -确实结过

1090
01:11:28,360 --> 01:11:29,559
But far less happy than you.
但远没有你那么幸福

1091
01:11:29,560 --> 01:11:32,239
How did he take that?
他是怎么想的

1092
01:11:32,240 --> 01:11:33,480
Not well.
不太能接受

1093
01:11:34,920 --> 01:11:39,080
He was trapped in a marriage with someone he didn't care for.
他跟不爱的人结了婚 困在婚姻里

1094
01:11:40,560 --> 01:11:43,679
He'd only gone through with it because it was expected of him,
他只能默默忍受 因为背负着这样的期待

1095
01:11:43,680 --> 01:11:45,679
and to please his family.
也为了让家人开心

1096
01:11:45,680 --> 01:11:48,680
So, that's where you were when you heard the gunshot.
所以听见枪声的时候你就在那里

1097
01:11:50,000 --> 01:11:52,439
And rather than having to answer any awkward questions
你们不愿意去回答那些令人尴尬的问题

1098
01:11:52,440 --> 01:11:53,999
about what you both were doing there,
你们俩在那里干嘛

1099
01:11:54,000 --> 01:11:55,480
you agreed to keep quiet about it.
于是决定保持沉默

1100
01:11:57,600 --> 01:11:59,319
Del begged me to meet him in town
Del求我第二天晚上和他见面

1101
01:11:59,320 --> 01:12:02,000
the following evening to finish our talk.
好继续我们的谈话

1102
01:12:03,120 --> 01:12:05,920
I'm afraid I left him with no illusions.
但我没给他留下任何幻想

1103
01:12:09,160 --> 01:12:10,440
Or hope.
或者希望

1104
01:12:17,840 --> 01:12:20,319
Does Mrs Appleby know about your, erm...
Appleby太太知道你们

1105
01:12:20,320 --> 01:12:22,319
.. "youthful indiscretion"?
年轻时的冲动吗

1106
01:12:22,320 --> 01:12:24,719
No, of course not.
当然不知道

1107
01:12:24,720 --> 01:12:26,519
Right, well, thank you.
好吧 谢谢你

1108
01:12:26,520 --> 01:12:29,160
We'll be in touch if we need any more information.
如果需要更多信息我们会联系你

1109
01:13:19,440 --> 01:13:21,760
I'm after Dinner For Three.
我要找《三人晚餐》

1110
01:13:28,080 --> 01:13:30,320
Outside, all of you!
出去 全都出去

1111
01:13:36,720 --> 01:13:38,799
I know you've been a long time out of the Smoke, Fred,
我知道你离开伦敦很久了 Fred

1112
01:13:38,800 --> 01:13:40,519
but it's still manners to pay your respects
但还是要讲点礼貌

1113
01:13:40,520 --> 01:13:42,119
when you come on somebody else's patch.
来到别人的地盘要拜拜码头吧

1114
01:13:42,120 --> 01:13:45,119
-I didn't like to bother you, Len.  -It's no bother.
-我不想麻烦你 Len  -不麻烦

1115
01:13:45,120 --> 01:13:48,199
And it's Commander Dury these days. Oh...
现在要叫我Dury长官了

1116
01:13:48,200 --> 01:13:49,520
For what it's worth.
就是这样

1117
01:13:50,680 --> 01:13:52,520
You've been talking to Ches Finch.
你找Ches Finch聊过了

1118
01:13:53,520 --> 01:13:55,800
Well, we were probationers together.
我们以前一起做过保释官

1119
01:13:56,760 --> 01:13:57,999
At Cable Street.
在Cable警局

1120
01:13:58,000 --> 01:14:00,439
The Dirty Squad falls under my eye these days.
扫黄组现在归我管了

1121
01:14:00,440 --> 01:14:03,519
-What's your interest?  -A murder with a link to blue films
-你想干嘛  -有桩谋杀案与色情电影有关

1122
01:14:03,520 --> 01:14:07,440
sold by a firm called The Ostrich Fanciers' Club.
是一家叫鸵鸟爱好者俱乐部的公司发售的

1123
01:14:08,920 --> 01:14:10,680
How it is, Fred.
这样吧 Fred

1124
01:14:11,880 --> 01:14:14,799
We've got it just how the upstairs like it.
我们保证让上级刚好满意

1125
01:14:14,800 --> 01:14:16,639
Nice and quiet, no trouble.
安静稳当 不作妖

1126
01:14:16,640 --> 01:14:18,319
Sure.
好

1127
01:14:18,320 --> 01:14:20,919
DI Nesbitt and DS Sneed will put the word out.
Nesbitt探员和Sneed探长会把话放出去

1128
01:14:20,920 --> 01:14:24,279
If it's some interloper, you can have them.
如果真的有人搞事 就交给你

1129
01:14:24,280 --> 01:14:25,519
If not...?
如果没有

1130
01:14:25,520 --> 01:14:27,999
Tell them they're looking for a shitehawk
告诉他们 要找的这个混蛋

1131
01:14:28,000 --> 01:14:30,920
in a trilby with an orange feather. About your size.
戴着橙色羽毛装饰的呢帽 跟你身材差不多

1132
01:14:32,560 --> 01:14:34,319
When did you blackmail Mahoney?
你什么时候敲诈Mahoney的

1133
01:14:34,320 --> 01:14:36,319
When he was prison chaplain at Wandsworth?
他在Wandsworth当监狱牧师的时候吗

1134
01:14:36,320 --> 01:14:38,079
What do you have on him? Boys, was it?
你有他什么把柄 恋童是吗

1135
01:14:38,080 --> 01:14:39,679
The flesh is weak.
人是软弱的

1136
01:14:39,680 --> 01:14:41,439
So, you put the squeeze on,
所以你向他施压

1137
01:14:41,440 --> 01:14:44,560
he fronts up your racket beyond the Smoke.
让他负责你在伦敦之外的那些勾当

1138
01:14:45,920 --> 01:14:50,239
From time to time, you drop by, posing as his half-brother Donal,
你假装他的继兄弟Donal 时不时去找他

1139
01:14:50,240 --> 01:14:52,599
to keep an eye on proceedings.
盯着他的行动

1140
01:14:52,600 --> 01:14:53,959
Is there a real Donal?
真的有Donal这个人吗

1141
01:14:53,960 --> 01:14:56,559
Or was that just for someone who might ask questions?
还是说只是编出来应付别人的好奇心

1142
01:14:56,560 --> 01:14:58,639
Like his housekeeper, for instance.
比如说他的管家

1143
01:14:58,640 --> 01:15:00,999
I could hardly show her my warrant card, could I?
我又不能给她看我的警官证 是吧

1144
01:15:01,000 --> 01:15:02,919
What happened, Len?
发生了什么 Len

1145
01:15:02,920 --> 01:15:05,239
You were a good thief-taker once.
你以前是坏蛋克星

1146
01:15:05,240 --> 01:15:08,360
We're none of us as clean as we'd like the world to think, eh?
我们倒希望世人看我们是清白的 但谁有那么清白呢

1147
01:15:11,240 --> 01:15:12,520
Well...
好吧

1148
01:15:13,920 --> 01:15:16,800
..the priest is dead now, whoever did for him.
不管是谁干的 牧师已经死了

1149
01:15:17,960 --> 01:15:20,880
The way I read it, I've got three men dead...
在我看来 现在有三个人死了

1150
01:15:21,840 --> 01:15:24,599
..all connected to your little caper.
全都跟你的非法勾当有关

1151
01:15:24,600 --> 01:15:27,559
Maybe someone's decided to put you out of business.
也许是有人想把你踢出这一行

1152
01:15:27,560 --> 01:15:29,159
I'll be seeing you.
回头见

1153
01:15:29,160 --> 01:15:30,880
Fred...
Fred

1154
01:15:33,320 --> 01:15:34,959
Your card's marked.
你已经被盯上了

1155
01:15:34,960 --> 01:15:36,600
For old times.
看在老交情的份上

1156
01:15:38,160 --> 01:15:39,639
Don't come back.
别再来了

1157
01:15:39,640 --> 01:15:42,280
What you do in your sewer is your concern.
你在这下三滥的地方干什么是你的事

1158
01:15:43,400 --> 01:15:46,039
You can be king of the shit heap for all it means to me.
在我看来 你在下水沟里称王称霸都随便

1159
01:15:46,040 --> 01:15:48,640
But you set foot on my ground again...
但你要是再踏上我的地盘

1160
01:15:49,680 --> 01:15:51,160
..you'll all swing.
你们死定了

1161
01:15:52,160 --> 01:15:54,600
I don't care whose coat you're carrying.
我不管你上头有什么人

1162
01:17:00,760 --> 01:17:02,559
-Ah, Morse.  -Sir.
-Morse  -长官

1163
01:17:02,560 --> 01:17:05,119
-Developments?  -Some, sir.
-有进展吗  -有一些 长官

1164
01:17:05,120 --> 01:17:06,759
I think we can rule out the passenger
我们应该可以排除

1165
01:17:06,760 --> 01:17:08,399
that Lunn picked up at the station.
Lunn在车站接到的那个乘客

1166
01:17:08,400 --> 01:17:10,680
How so? Oh, may I offer you...?
怎么说 要来一杯

1167
01:17:12,040 --> 01:17:14,760
Yes, sir. Whisky, if I may.
好的 长官 威士忌 谢谢

1168
01:17:16,520 --> 01:17:19,719
-What's this?  -What?
-这是什么  -什么

1169
01:17:19,720 --> 01:17:22,600
Oh, well, it's just a... Just a hobby.
哦 这个啊 只是个爱好

1170
01:17:25,240 --> 01:17:27,999
-These are very good, sir.  -Oh, thank you.
-画得特别好 长官  -谢谢

1171
01:17:28,000 --> 01:17:30,239
Clearing out my wife's clothes,
清理我妻子的衣服的时候

1172
01:17:30,240 --> 01:17:32,799
I found my old watercolour box at the back of the wardrobe.
我在衣柜后面找到了以前的水彩盒

1173
01:17:32,800 --> 01:17:34,080
You were saying?
你刚刚说什么

1174
01:17:36,160 --> 01:17:38,719
Oh, yes, she appears to have been his mistress.
哦对 她好像是他的情妇

1175
01:17:38,720 --> 01:17:42,360
He dropped her at home at 9:20 to a beating from her husband.
他9点20把她送回到家 然后她被丈夫打了

1176
01:17:45,560 --> 01:17:47,240
Who is she?
她是谁

1177
01:17:48,440 --> 01:17:50,039
Oh, yes, Miss Parry.
是Parry小姐

1178
01:17:50,040 --> 01:17:51,639
Life model at the art school.
美术学校里的绘画模特

1179
01:17:51,640 --> 01:17:53,839
Yes, she's quite striking, isn't she?
她很美 是吧

1180
01:17:53,840 --> 01:17:55,200
Cheers.
干杯

1181
01:18:49,480 --> 01:18:51,239
Miss Parry?
Parry小姐

1182
01:18:51,240 --> 01:18:52,640
Yes.
对

1183
01:18:55,040 --> 01:18:57,079
And what time would that have been?
那是什么时候

1184
01:18:57,080 --> 01:18:59,719
Oh, I finished about nine o'clock.
我是九点左右结束的

1185
01:18:59,720 --> 01:19:01,359
Ah, good morning, sir.
早上好 长官

1186
01:19:01,360 --> 01:19:05,519
Sir, do you remember Mr Roberts, the dispatcher from Speedy Cabs?
长官 你记得Roberts先生吗 极速出租车的调度员

1187
01:19:05,520 --> 01:19:07,039
He's very kindly offered to come in
今天早上他过来

1188
01:19:07,040 --> 01:19:09,039
and help us out with a statement this morning.
帮我们录一份口供

1189
01:19:09,040 --> 01:19:12,439
-A statement?  -Just a small matter concerning timings.
-口供  -就问点时间上的事

1190
01:19:12,440 --> 01:19:15,559
Mr Roberts, can you tell us what time
Roberts先生 你让Joe North去

1191
01:19:15,560 --> 01:19:20,039
did you give Joe North the job to pick up Mrs Maynard from her house?
Maynard太太家接她是几点

1192
01:19:20,040 --> 01:19:22,159
Mid-afternoon. 3:30, four o'clock.
下午三点多 三点半 四点的样子

1193
01:19:22,160 --> 01:19:24,599
Right. And was that over the telephone or...?
是打的电话还是

1194
01:19:24,600 --> 01:19:25,839
No, he popped into the office.
不是 他去了趟办公室

1195
01:19:25,840 --> 01:19:29,879
Most of the fellas do around that time, you know, if they're slack.
那个时间 小伙子们没什么事的话都会过去

1196
01:19:29,880 --> 01:19:32,239
And Speedy Cabs, they sponsor a table
极速出租车为Maynard准将举办的

1197
01:19:32,240 --> 01:19:34,519
at Commodore Maynard's lodge charity nights.
共济会地方分会慈善晚宴提供赞助

1198
01:19:34,520 --> 01:19:36,240
-Is that right?  -Oh, yes.
-是吗  -是的

1199
01:19:37,360 --> 01:19:39,999
Now, would Joe North have ever gone to those events?
Joe North参加过这种活动吗

1200
01:19:40,000 --> 01:19:42,639
Oh, we've all been to one or two of those.
我们都去过一两次啊

1201
01:19:42,640 --> 01:19:44,040
Joe included.
Joe也一样

1202
01:19:45,840 --> 01:19:48,839
You don't think he's involved, do you? Not Joe!
你不会觉得是他吧 Joe不可能的

1203
01:19:48,840 --> 01:19:51,119
Why, I can't believe it.
我不信

1204
01:19:51,120 --> 01:19:53,839
Sir, do you remember that we found Commodore Maynard's body
长官 您还记不记得 我们是在一个落地摆钟前发现的

1205
01:19:53,840 --> 01:19:55,479
in front of the grandfather clock?
Maynard准将的尸体

1206
01:19:55,480 --> 01:19:57,639
The key was on the floor next to him.
钥匙在他身旁的地板上

1207
01:19:57,640 --> 01:20:00,359
-The glass door was open so he could wind it.  -Exactly.
-玻璃门开着 是为了给钟上发条  -没错

1208
01:20:00,360 --> 01:20:03,199
His wife told us he always wound the clocks at 9:00.
他妻子说他一般会在9点给钟上发条

1209
01:20:03,200 --> 01:20:04,599
-Right.  -So, we've been lucky,
-对  -那我们就很幸运了

1210
01:20:04,600 --> 01:20:06,519
insofar as we've been able to establish
可以确定这几个谋杀案

1211
01:20:06,520 --> 01:20:08,639
at what time each of the murders took place.
发生的时间

1212
01:20:10,760 --> 01:20:12,640
Dudley Lunn just before 10:00.
Dudley Lunn差不多是10点

1213
01:20:13,800 --> 01:20:15,040
Father Mahoney at 8:00.
Mahoney神父是八点

1214
01:20:16,360 --> 01:20:18,279
And Commodore Maynard at 9:00.
Maynard准将是9点

1215
01:20:18,280 --> 01:20:19,639
Which tells us...
这就说明

1216
01:20:19,640 --> 01:20:22,839
..that the killer changed the time on a watch or clock
在每一个犯罪现场 凶手都调整了

1217
01:20:22,840 --> 01:20:24,639
at each of the scene of crimes.
手表或者时钟的时间

1218
01:20:24,640 --> 01:20:26,919
So, at ten o'clock,
他把Dudley Lunn的

1219
01:20:26,920 --> 01:20:30,559
he changed Dudley Lunn's watch to 6:50.
手表从10点调成6点50分

1220
01:20:30,560 --> 01:20:34,319
At eight o'clock, he changed Father Mahoney's pocket watch to 3:50.
把Mahoney神父的怀表从8点调成3点50分

1221
01:20:34,320 --> 01:20:36,359
And at nine o'clock,
把Maynard准将的

1222
01:20:36,360 --> 01:20:39,959
he changed Commodore Maynard's carriage clock to 3:10.
马车钟从9点调成3点10分

1223
01:20:39,960 --> 01:20:42,519
Now, we thought that he was trying to just supply himself
我们之前以为他是想给自己制造假的不在场证明

1224
01:20:42,520 --> 01:20:45,839
with a false alibi. But it's actually far, far simpler than that.
但其实没那么复杂

1225
01:20:45,840 --> 01:20:47,359
If you say so.
愿闻其详

1226
01:20:47,360 --> 01:20:49,560
The actual time is immaterial.
时间是几点并不重要

1227
01:20:50,760 --> 01:20:54,160
It's the position of the hands on the clock that's important.
重要的是时针分针的位置

1228
01:20:55,240 --> 01:20:57,999
To use the terminology that was drilled into us in Signals.
用我们学的信号术语来说

1229
01:20:58,000 --> 01:21:00,799
6:50, left hand down, right hand high.
6点50分 左手下垂 右手在右上方

1230
01:21:00,800 --> 01:21:03,719
3:50, left hand out, right hand high.
3点50分 左手平举 右手在右上方

1231
01:21:03,720 --> 01:21:06,839
3:10, left hand out, right hand across high.
3点10分 左手平举 右手过头顶在左上方

1232
01:21:06,840 --> 01:21:08,479
-Semaphore?  -Exactly.
-旗语  -没错

1233
01:21:08,480 --> 01:21:10,839
Mine's a bit rusty, but C-Y-W?
我有点忘了 是C Y W吗

1234
01:21:10,840 --> 01:21:12,199
C-Y-W, yes.
对 C Y W

1235
01:21:13,520 --> 01:21:15,079
It doesn't mean anything.
没什么含义啊

1236
01:21:15,080 --> 01:21:17,520
No, well, it's a puzzle, isn't it?
不太能理解 是吧

1237
01:21:18,480 --> 01:21:20,080
Ah, Miss Parry.
啊 Parry小姐

1238
01:21:26,080 --> 01:21:28,360
Fy nghyw bach!
Fy nghyw bach

1239
01:21:31,480 --> 01:21:32,760
Oh...!
噢

1240
01:21:40,240 --> 01:21:41,520
Cyw...
Cyw

1241
01:21:43,280 --> 01:21:45,039
Thank you, Miss Parry, for coming in
Parry小姐 感谢你过来

1242
01:21:45,040 --> 01:21:47,199
to confirm what you confided in me earlier.
证实了之前跟我说过的话

1243
01:21:47,200 --> 01:21:49,759
Constable, if you can escort her to the canteen,
警员 麻烦带她去食堂那边

1244
01:21:49,760 --> 01:21:51,000
I'll see you in a moment.
我一会就过去

1245
01:21:52,800 --> 01:21:55,639
Yes, of course, sir, you're right. C-Y-W doesn't mean anything.
长官 您说得没错 CYW在英语里

1246
01:21:55,640 --> 01:21:57,159
In English.
是没什么含义

1247
01:21:57,160 --> 01:21:58,400
But in Welsh...
但在威尔士语里

1248
01:21:59,360 --> 01:22:02,839
..and perhaps you can help me with my pronunciation here,
我要是发音不对 你可以纠正我

1249
01:22:02,840 --> 01:22:05,440
cyw is a term of endearment.
cyw是一种爱称

1250
01:22:06,480 --> 01:22:08,199
It means "chick".
意为宝贝

1251
01:22:08,200 --> 01:22:09,999
Now, you said to us...
你之前跟我们说

1252
01:22:10,000 --> 01:22:11,520
.."This is Siwan.
这是Siwan

1253
01:22:12,520 --> 01:22:14,720
"Joan, she'd be in English.
英语里是Joan

1254
01:22:15,680 --> 01:22:18,239
"But most people call her Birdie." Yes?
但很多人都叫她小黄莺 对吧

1255
01:22:18,240 --> 01:22:20,200
So she was to everyone else.
别人是这么叫她

1256
01:22:21,200 --> 01:22:22,560
But to me...
但对我来说

1257
01:22:23,520 --> 01:22:24,640
..fy nghyw bach.
fy nghyw bach

1258
01:22:25,960 --> 01:22:27,360
My little chick.
她就是我的小宝贝

1259
01:22:28,680 --> 01:22:29,759
Cyw.
Cyw

1260
01:22:29,760 --> 01:22:31,079
I recognised her
长官 我看到

1261
01:22:31,080 --> 01:22:33,759
from Superintendent Bright's sketchpad, sir.
Bright警司的画板才认出了她

1262
01:22:33,760 --> 01:22:35,919
Although she now calls herself Lynn Parry,
虽然她现在随了她母亲的姓

1263
01:22:35,920 --> 01:22:37,560
after her mother's maiden name.
自称为Lynn Parry

1264
01:22:40,800 --> 01:22:43,960
She's also the blonde in the blue films made with Dudley Lunn.
但她就是那个和Dudley Lunn一起拍色情片的金发女郎

1265
01:22:49,120 --> 01:22:52,959
Ifan Roberts, I'm arresting you for the murder of Dudley Lunn,
Ifan Roberts 你因谋杀Dudley Lunn 

1266
01:22:52,960 --> 01:22:55,040
Father Mahoney and Commodore Maynard.
Mahoney神父和Maynard准将被逮捕了

1267
01:22:57,720 --> 01:23:00,760
Presumably you watched Lunn for a long time.
你应该盯了Lunn很长时间吧

1268
01:23:02,280 --> 01:23:04,200
Planning, waiting for your moment.
然后伺机而动

1269
01:23:06,640 --> 01:23:08,600
You knew he was knocking off Patty Grady.
你知道他和Patty Grady有一腿

1270
01:23:09,520 --> 01:23:13,240
And you knew that Mr Grady worked at Paradise Court.
也知道Grady先生在天堂院上班

1271
01:23:15,520 --> 01:23:17,720
I watched them all for a month, on and off.
他们几个我断断续续盯了一个月

1272
01:23:19,960 --> 01:23:21,760
Nobody notices taxis.
没人会注意出租车

1273
01:23:23,080 --> 01:23:25,840
Get behind the wheel of a cab and you might as well be invisible.
开出租还是降低存在感的好

1274
01:23:26,960 --> 01:23:28,640
But we see everything.
但我们什么都知道

1275
01:23:31,280 --> 01:23:32,959
The pathetic secrets.
可悲的小秘密

1276
01:23:32,960 --> 01:23:34,680
The carrying on.
令人不齿的勾当

1277
01:23:35,760 --> 01:23:37,040
All of it.
全都知道

1278
01:23:38,480 --> 01:23:41,959
As a dispatcher, you were perfectly placed
你作为调度员 给Lunn派个假活

1279
01:23:41,960 --> 01:23:45,199
to send Lunn on a non-existent job to Hovelle Wood,
让他去Hovelle树林 并不是什么难事

1280
01:23:45,200 --> 01:23:47,879
where you would be waiting for him.
然后你就在那等着他

1281
01:23:47,880 --> 01:23:50,959
Ifan, what's...?
Ifan 你

1282
01:23:50,960 --> 01:23:52,600
What's this about?
你这是要干什么

1283
01:23:56,320 --> 01:23:59,639
See what you did, Dudley, to my Siwan!
Dudley 看看你对我的Siwan都干了些什么

1284
01:23:59,640 --> 01:24:02,279
-Eh? Tell me who else is involved!  -No-one.
-告诉我还有谁  -没别人了

1285
01:24:02,280 --> 01:24:03,519
Tell me!
说

1286
01:24:03,520 --> 01:24:07,840
You probably told him he'd live if he gave you what you wanted.
你告诉他 说出名字就饶他一命

1287
01:24:16,840 --> 01:24:20,160
How did you discover your daughter was involved?
你怎么发现你女儿牵涉其中的

1288
01:24:23,840 --> 01:24:25,119
Oh...
噢

1289
01:24:25,120 --> 01:24:27,800
I see. Of course.
我知道了

1290
01:24:29,880 --> 01:24:33,280
You'd become a member of The Ostrich Fanciers' Club.
你是鸵鸟爱好者俱乐部的会员

1291
01:24:35,120 --> 01:24:37,679
You'd ordered some of their films.
你买了他们的片子

1292
01:24:37,680 --> 01:24:40,000
You saw her.
然后看到了她

1293
01:24:44,440 --> 01:24:45,920
I knew her at once.
我一眼就认出了她

1294
01:24:47,280 --> 01:24:49,200
She was my little girl.
她是我的女儿

1295
01:24:50,840 --> 01:24:52,560
Fy nghyw bach!
我的小宝贝

1296
01:25:01,680 --> 01:25:04,079
He was just a name on a card twice a year.
他对我来说不过是卡片上的名字 一年见两次

1297
01:25:04,080 --> 01:25:05,560
"Love, Dad."
爱你的爸爸

1298
01:25:07,200 --> 01:25:09,479
Dad? What does that even mean?
爸爸 这到底意味着什么呢

1299
01:25:09,480 --> 01:25:11,359
I barely remember him.
我对他都没什么印象

1300
01:25:11,360 --> 01:25:13,719
Perhaps. But he never forgot you.
也许吧 但他从未忘记过你

1301
01:25:13,720 --> 01:25:16,240
Well, maybe it would have been better for everyone if he had.
说不定他忘了对大家都好

1302
01:25:17,240 --> 01:25:20,680
Something far easier said than done for any father.
对每个父亲来说 有些事是说起来容易做起来难

1303
01:25:21,720 --> 01:25:22,960
What can you think of me?
你会怎么看我

1304
01:25:24,120 --> 01:25:27,039
I think you're an intelligent, sensitive, young woman
我觉得你年轻 聪明 体贴

1305
01:25:27,040 --> 01:25:29,000
who fell amongst scoundrels.
只是没遇上好人

1306
01:25:30,200 --> 01:25:32,560
Any shame is on their side.
该羞愧的是他们

1307
01:25:34,160 --> 01:25:35,680
Not yours.
不是你

1308
01:25:44,560 --> 01:25:45,760
Thank you.
谢谢你

1309
01:26:05,480 --> 01:26:07,999
45, 45, pick up
45号 45号 新订单

1310
01:26:08,000 --> 01:26:11,320
98B Chestnut Way, New Hinkley.
从新辛克利栗树路98B号

1311
01:26:12,600 --> 01:26:13,759
Going to...
到

1312
01:26:13,760 --> 01:26:16,119
..North Oxford Lawn Tennis Club.
北牛津草场网球俱乐部

1313
01:26:16,120 --> 01:26:18,440
Passenger's a Miss Carlitt.
乘客是Carlitt小姐

1314
01:26:19,720 --> 01:26:22,279
Yeah, Roger, Clarry. On way.
收到 Clarry 我出发了

1315
01:26:53,920 --> 01:26:55,479
I should've tumbled.
我早该想到的

1316
01:26:55,480 --> 01:26:57,279
Crossed flags on his arm.
他手臂上纹的交叉旗

1317
01:26:57,280 --> 01:26:59,319
It's the badge of a Naval signalman.
是海军信号员的标志

1318
01:26:59,320 --> 01:27:01,679
And what of the graffiti?
那墙上的字呢

1319
01:27:01,680 --> 01:27:04,319
Micah.5.15.
弥迦书第五章第十五节

1320
01:27:04,320 --> 01:27:08,999
"And I will execute vengeance with anger and fury upon the heathen
我必在盛怒之下 向那不听从的

1321
01:27:09,000 --> 01:27:10,839
"such as they have not heard."
异教徒施报

1322
01:27:10,840 --> 01:27:13,199
He did it in her name. I can't say I blame him.
他是为了她才这么做的 也不能怪他

1323
01:27:13,200 --> 01:27:15,679
-If it had been my daughter...  -Ah, but it never would be.
-要是我女儿的话  -那不可能

1324
01:27:15,680 --> 01:27:17,559
It could happen to anyone.
发生在谁身上都有可能

1325
01:27:17,560 --> 01:27:19,159
Given the right circumstances.
如果是在特定的情形下

1326
01:27:19,160 --> 01:27:20,919
They're all somebody's daughter.
她们会是别人的女儿

1327
01:27:20,920 --> 01:27:22,839
Somebody's mother, sister.
母亲 姐妹

1328
01:27:22,840 --> 01:27:24,960
They all mean something to someone.
有人会在乎她们

1329
01:27:26,120 --> 01:27:27,480
Or did once.
或者说在乎过她们

1330
01:27:28,640 --> 01:27:30,599
And now because of The Ostrich Fanciers' Club,
现在因为鸵鸟爱好者俱乐部

1331
01:27:30,600 --> 01:27:31,840
they mean nothing to anyone.
没人在乎她们了

1332
01:27:33,080 --> 01:27:34,160
Except to us.
除了我们

1333
01:27:35,600 --> 01:27:37,400
They mean something to us.
我们在乎她们

1334
01:27:39,480 --> 01:27:40,800
To me, at least.
至少我是如此

1335
01:27:42,680 --> 01:27:45,279
I'd have said to you, too, once.
以前我也跟你说过

1336
01:27:45,280 --> 01:27:47,040
Well, I'm not the fool I was.
我不像以前那么蠢了

1337
01:27:49,840 --> 01:27:51,480
I quite liked that fool.
我还挺喜欢以前的你

1338
01:27:52,920 --> 01:27:54,560
He hoped for the best in people.
愿意把人往好处想

1339
01:27:56,160 --> 01:27:59,960
Surely, it's better to see things as they are.
还是实事求是点好

1340
01:28:02,400 --> 01:28:05,759
People make bad choices, they have to pay the consequences.
人们做错了选择 就要承担后果

1341
01:28:05,760 --> 01:28:06,999
What about pity, understanding?
那同情 理解呢

1342
01:28:07,000 --> 01:28:08,839
Where does that fit into the picture?
都不考虑吗

1343
01:28:08,840 --> 01:28:10,919
I'm not here to...
我该做的事

1344
01:28:10,920 --> 01:28:12,400
..kiss the wounded.
不是抚慰伤痛

1345
01:28:13,520 --> 01:28:15,360
I'm here to make sure justice gets done.
伸张正义才是我的职责所在

1346
01:28:16,800 --> 01:28:18,879
The rest I can leave to the likes of Father Mahoney,
其余的就交给Mahoney神父那样的人吧

1347
01:28:18,880 --> 01:28:20,000
for all the good it did him.
虽然他也没落得什么好下场

1348
01:28:21,160 --> 01:28:22,560
Well...
那

1349
01:28:24,280 --> 01:28:25,920
..I'm sure you know best.
你自己想清楚就行

1350
01:28:31,560 --> 01:28:33,639
Another beer? Or are you bitter enough?
再来一杯 还是就此打住

1351
01:28:35,000 --> 01:28:37,320
No, I won't. I've got something on tonight.
不喝了 我晚上还有事

1352
01:28:39,400 --> 01:28:41,040
We're who we are, Morse.
人的本性是不会改变的 Morse

1353
01:28:42,520 --> 01:28:44,480
Our nature...
再怎么逃离

1354
01:28:45,840 --> 01:28:48,000
..we can try to escape it.
我们最终还是会

1355
01:28:49,080 --> 01:28:50,880
But it'll find us out in the end.
回归本性

1356
01:28:52,640 --> 01:28:54,399
A man's what he is.
不论是否愿意

1357
01:28:54,400 --> 01:28:56,120
Whether he likes it or not.
你就是你
							
 
